B00DDL7A60.title: The Friendly Swede (TM) Trilobite Extra Beefy / Wide 500 lb Paracord Survival Bracelet With Stainless Steel Black Bow Shackle - Adjustable Size Fits 7-8 Inch Wrists - In Retail Packaging - Lifetime Warranty
B00DDL7A60.Best review: The Friendly Swede's wide "extra beefy" paracord survival bracelet (with bow shackle connector) is a good next-size-up version of their premium paracord bracelet. It's wider (and carries an additional 1.5' of cord), and has all the functionality I expect from something like this.If you have to use the cord itself, it's 11.5 ft of paracord tightly braided into a 9" bracelet design. The clasp, while a bit difficult to get connected the first time, is adjustable and *very* secure once fastened. The bracelet starts out stiff, but loosens up after a couple of wearings (or with manual flexing back and forth for a bit). The reason the clasp can be difficult is that you're essentially having to put it on with a single hand while trying to position and line up the holes. I found that after two or three practice runs, it wasn't that difficult, plus the bracelet was more flexible and "compliant" to go where I wanted.The Friendly Swede will also replace the bracelet if you actually need to disassemble it and use the cord for any reason. It's this type of customer service that makes the company a pleasure to deal with.If you are looking at something like this as a "fashion statement", then keep in mind that this version is more chunky than the premium version. But for actual use in the real world, this is a good choice as you get more cord in the same easy-to-use functional design.The paracord bracelet is a definite "should-have" for any camping or outdoor adventure, and it's not a bad idea to buy two or three to have spares to stock in an emergency kit. It's a good amount of paracord (and bow shackle) in a small and functional package.Disclosure:Obtained From: RetailerPayment: Free

B00CMTM9XI.description: CREE XM-L2 LED, delivering a maximum output of 900 ANSI lumens. Patented Tail-cap & Side Switch design, allowing easy access to power settings. Easy-access Strobe feature can activated at any time, Ergonomically designed for one-handed operation. Specifically designed tail cap allows upright 'Candle' hands-free use. Waterproof design rated to IPX-8 (waterproof to a depth of 2 meters). Stainless Steel bezel design protects the lens and reflector system from drops and impacts. Intelligent control circuits balance brightness, run-time and heat emission for improved performance. Optical lens system allows for illumination up to 100 meters. Anti-shortcut design prevents accidental damage to internal electronics.
B00CMTM9XI.title: Klarus ST11 XM-L2 U2 Cree LED Flashlight, Grey
B00CMTM9XI.Best review: There is no doubt that Klarus makes excellent lights I have the XT2C also and both lights are excellent in workmanship and performance. To me their user interface is a problem. I probably like the user interface on the the XT2C better than this one, but even the XT2C interface is not near as simple and user friendly as the Fenix or Olight.This ST11 has a very impressive light output, it is about the same as the Fenix PD35 which has 850 Lumens. The Fenix is a lot smaller and nicer design as the Klarus and to me you cannot beat the Fenix easily understandable and user friendly interface. So far the Fenix PD35 is my favorite light, but the Klarus for the price is a very good value and I will definitely keep it in my collection.I am now waiting for the Olight M22 Warrior kit and I will probably update this review after the comparisons. One thing is fact that the Olights also have a very simple, easily understandable user interface with less (but enough) options for the light outputs than the Fenix. I also have Olight M18 Maverick and I love it with the impressive 500 Lumens output and it's sleek design which is the smallest and the lightest in the bunch I have. It became my favorite all around light.Just to make it clear and do not get me wrong I like this Flashlight a lot it is a fine (and heavy) Flash light and I recommend it to anybody to get one of the absolute brightest lights you can find especially for the price, but get ready with a little frustration especially at the beginning when you start using it.

B003VUIXX2.description: Have you ever thought that it is difficult for you to fumble in the dark looking for the keys or an item on the nightstand? B003VUIXX2.title: Blocklite (TM) Mini Compact Size Ultra Bright 9V LED Flashlight for Camping, Indoor Use

B004Y7GZG8.description: The JETBeam BC40 is one of the world's brightest flashlights in its class. The BC40 uses the most advance LED technology available today. Incorporating a premium CREE 10 watt XM-L T6 LED with a life span of 50,000 hours, the BC40 has a max output of 830 lumens that can throw a high intensity beam up to 344 meters. If you need lower output for close-up work or just want longer battery life the BC40 has a built in smart fast switching system that can easily switch the light in to low mode with a run time up to 11 hours simply by loosening the flashlight bezel. In low output mode, the BC40 puts out 130 lumens that throws the beam up to 115 meters. Powering the BC40 are a choice of either 4 x CR123 or 2 x 18650 lithium batteries. Featuring the JETBeam advanced power source regulated circuitry, the BC40 emits a steady consistent non-flickering beam for the duration of the battery in either high or low mode.
B004Y7GZG8.title: JETBeam XM-L LED 830 Lumen Flashlight, Black
B004Y7GZG8.Best review: IMO and those of many expert reviewers this is one of the best bargains in the LED flashlight market today. You have to accept a simple 2 mode interface, but the BC40 equals or betters the performance of lights costing two or three times as much. Yet it still offers excellent build quality and a light output & throw distance that will produce that Shock & Awe Factor in anyone. More light than anyone probably will ever really need, but that's what makes it fun! If you want to own one of the brightest flashlights on the market at a bargain price this is your ticket!

B000FLESYI.description: The New, 3 L.E.D. Touch 'N Lite is Garrity's latest addition to its growing line of L.E.D. flashlights and lanterns and another first. Blazing the path, not following, is the Garrity way. While others imitate, Garrity innovates. Lifetime warranty on the fixture only not to include bulbs and batteries.
B000FLESYI.title: Garrity L.E.D. Touch Lite Bright 3 Led Battery Operated Lamp, Great for Closets, Attics, Garages

B003VTY2OM.description: Fit one of these and your torch it's instantly transformed into a lantern capable of lighting a whole room or tent. Made from a heat resistant, high impact material (PC 2805) this simple and effective device is a must have item for all Fenix torch owners. Easy to fit and remove. Great light distribution.I used it for cooking at night while camping.  Worked great.  I hung the flashlight by the lanyard with the diffuser, on a little post by my cooking station.  When i say we were cooking, we had a lot of ingredients sitting around the table and this diffuser helped a ton.  There were no dark areas around my cooking station so i could identify everything and cook very well in the dead of night.  Then took it into my tent, hung it inside there while getting ready to hit the hay.  Once again, it worked great.I would highly recommend this as a replacement/switchout for a lantern that people usually bring.  Your flashlight can duel as a lantern (with this diffuser) and it takes up much less space and a ton lighter (just a peice of plactic)...especially for you folks that backpack/hike into your camping grounds.Finally, the diffuser is of good quality and fits nice and snug on my Fenix LD20.  It fits snug enough that it cannot be shaken off...you have to pull at it with some force to get the diffuser off which is a good thing.Two thumbs up hereCheers

B007BP9YC2.description: The Larry 8 LED Pocket Work Light is the essential handyman light. 8 powerful LEDs provide 60 lumens of bright white light. B007BP9YC2.title: NEBO Larry 8 LED Pocket Work Flashlight

B001GAOOH8.title: Fenix P2D 6 Level High Performance Cree LED Flashlight

B002QIQ80K.description: Saint Minimus™ is a virtually indestructible headlamp offering a low profile and weight. It's powered by one 123A lithium battery that screws right into the housing utilizing Minimus's single-battery cap. Dial Minimus from 0 to 100 lumens, and all points in between, with a simple twist. Cut from hard-anodized aerospace-grade aluminum, Minimus is built to survive and it is ultra lightweight and comfortable to wear due, in part, to its custom-made headband and moisture wicking Breathe-O-Prene pad. This is the virtually indestructible-yet ultra lightweight -headlamp you'd expect from SureFire.Includes one high-energy 123A batteries with 10-year shelf life..Output: High: 100 lumens.Low: 1 lumen.Runtime: High Setting: 1.5 hours.Low Setting: 50 hours.Weight: 3.3 ounces with battery.Size: 3.6"x 1.6" x 1.4".Batteries: One 123A lithium.
B002QIQ80K.title: Surefire Saint Minimus Headlamp
B002QIQ80K.Best review: I've owned every sort of headlamp imaginable and this is by far the best.  Ultra light weight, comfortable, rugged, rotary control brightness, floody neutral beam, no heat problems... I could go on and on...  If you have to wear a headlamp for your job or just like headlamps - do yourself a favor and buy this.  The whole thing reeks of quality and after having to put up with customer service from different companies when their $80 headlamps gave out, I'm going to stick to Surefire.  They've never let me down! You get what you pay for!!!

B00143JZ08.description: Looking for lots of power in an ultra compact, lightweight package? The Streamlight MicroStream LED Penlight is your answer. Make sure to check your pockets before doing your laundry.**Update** I read a reviewer claim he got 3.5 hours running AAA Eneloop rechargables. I tested it for myself and sure enough just around 3.5 hours! Very cool!

B000EDRTUW.description: With the Gerber Clutch mini-tool in your pocket or on your keychain, you'll be ready for action. This compact tool comes loaded with drivers, tweezers and a gerber blade. A serious tool in a small, convenient package.FeaturesStrong mini-pliersKeychain compatibleLightweight, anodized aluminum handlesOverall Length: 4.13" / 10.5 cmClosed Length: 2.56" / 6.5 cmWeight: 2.5 oz. / 63 gramsHandle Material - Anodized Aircraft AluminumComponents: Needlenose pliers, knife blade, file, nail cleaner, small and medium flat blade screwdrivers, crosspoint screwdriver, tweezers, bottle opener and key ring attachment.Pliers Type: Needlenose
B000EDRTUW.title: Gerber Clutch Mini Tool
B000EDRTUW.Best review: Useful combination of tools and great snap-shut design makes this tool sexy and you'll develop an attachment to it. However, there will also be heart ache, which for me was that the pliers snapped after about 6 months of use when I used a bit too much force on them one time. Given the quality, don't pay over $15 for it.

B000JV5XCA.description: The Swiss Army knife was built on the premise of portable functionality. With that thought in mind, Wenger developed the Swiss Clipper. Made of tempered stainless steel, this retractable precision instrument fits in your pocket. Great for home, hotel room or even in the great outdoors. Ingenious deployment lever lifts the tool out of the housing to avoid potential damage to your nails.Nail file..Nail cleaner..Toothpick..Tweezers..Key ring..Length 2.5 in..Wt. 1.3 oz..
B000JV5XCA.title: Wenger Swiss Clipper
B000JV5XCA.Best review: Wenger and Victorinox have both served as official suppliers to the Swiss Army.  As such, both continue a tradition of quality products and both are excellent - so choose the unit that supplies you with the tools you need most.  This Wenger unit (in red) is my "small" daily carry, as you don't really need a 6-inch blade in most urban environments, but you will be "attacked" regularly by boxes, letters, strings, tape, and other minor nuisances handled with ease by this unit.  It is small but a bit thicker than similar knives to accommodate the clippers. It includes the toothpick & tweezers in the handle. The scissors are lightly serrated (self-sharpening) and have a tougher return spring that some prefer over Victorinox.  The blade is not liked at the airports, so another model is available with a mini-eyeglasses screwdriver in place of the blade - or just check the bladed unit in your luggage.  The purple see-thru color is becoming somewhat rare and is a favorite among the ladies - it makes a nice birthday or graduation present.  Search "Wenger Clipper" for other colors, including an all stainless version at double the cost.  Note that most Wenger and Victorinox blades do not "lock-back" and proper handling is needed.  If you need something bigger, my favorite medium and large units are the Victorinox Huntsman or Champion Plus, and the SOG S10B Tech Bowie (TiNi black) or Team Leader Survivor TL-02 in AUS-8 steel (to preserve saw sharpness, vs. the cheaper/softer 440 stainless version).

B007FFV1W4.description: Waterproof and submersible this flashlight has a textured lens which produces broad, soft illumination.  The rubberized grip is shaped for easy one handed operation with the textured bezel being very easy to grasp and turn.  Includes a carbiner for easy attachment to your back pack, vest, tent, or wherever else you might find convenient.  A single, included AAA battery is all it takes to get almost 12 hours of steady light and 16 hours of flashing SOS signal from this great light .  Handy and practical!
B007FFV1W4.title: EGear Splash Flash LED Light
B007FFV1W4.Best review: Small lights that are very bright for the size. Waterproof has been tested. It worked perfectly and no issues since dunking it in a glass of water for about 2 minutes. I have 3 and they're clipped to the outside of my main BOB and 2 smaller bags. Simple operation also. One twist and you have a very bright area light. Twist it off and then right back on and you have the SOS light. Notice that I said it is an area light. This is not a direct beam flashlight.Recommended? Yes.

B003DQ0F0I.description: 4AA LED Lantern, 9 Super Brite LED's, Long Distanced Focused Beam, Plastic, Assorted Colors, Black, Red & Yellow, Includes 4 Heavy Duty "AA" Batteries, No Bulbs To Replace.
B003DQ0F0I.title: Dorcy International 41-1047 LED Lantern
B003DQ0F0I.Best review: I expected more light from a lamp with so many LED bulbs.Not better than a one AA battery-one bulb led flashlight.

B001GAOOHS.description: The Fenix P3D premium Q5 is a high-tech, rugged tool that's perfect for any lighting application. It features six levels of output, which not only allows the user to select the best compromise between brightness and runtime for any given task, but also has ability to aid in an emergency. The six output levels include dim, regular, high, SOS, turbo and strobe. When in turbo mode, the Fenix P3D throws an awesome 215 lumens beam, an incredible amount of light for a light of any size. If you're looking for a flashlight with solid reliability, digitally regulated brightness, and compact size, this Fenix is for you.
B001GAOOHS.title: Fenix P3D 6 Level High Performance Cree LED Flashlight
B001GAOOHS.Best review: I bought this light for emergency use. I picked this one because it's a lot cheaper than any Surefire flashlight, has multiple output settings, small, convenient, and uses the 5-10 year shelf life CR123A batteries. Since it's being used for emergencies, I needed a flashlight that was going to last a long time without being used much and also last long while it's being used. On it's lowest setting it will last continuously for 65 hours, great if you're in a disaster situation and in turbo mode, it's more than bright enough for signaling or searching. It is definitely one of the brightest flashlights I've found. The price is so much better than other flashlights at this output level. The surefire lights usually only have two lighting modes, aren't as bright and don't last as long and a lot more expensive, usually twice as much. So I've been able to buy two of these for the price of one surefire and leave the in the car and in our disaster pack.The only negatives is that the tail switch has no lockout for accidentally turning it on while in a purse or backpack and little protection for the lens.Another comment, The light is also round so it WILL roll off a flat surface.I find that i am using more often than i anticipated because it's so small, handy, and kinda fun to use at night while walking through the parking lot at night.Great light.PS. buy the batteries directly from Surefire.com, i haven't found them any cheaper anywhere else.

B0001WP5Z2.description: The E1E is an ultra compact flashlight. A special incandescent lamp assembly and a precision micro-textured reflector produce a smooth 15-lumen beam—the same output as many big two-D-cell flashlights. The pushbutton tailcap switch provides secure, ergonomic activation control: press for momentary-on, press further to click constant-on. Lightweight enough to clip to the brim of a cap for hands-free operation.
B0001WP5Z2.title: Surefire E1E Executive Elite Single-Output Incandescent Flashlight, Black
B0001WP5Z2.Best review: The Surefire E1E I own probably gets more use than any other flashlight. It is not bright enough for defense, running about 15 lumens, but as a handy go anywhere flashlight it is superb. I have carried mine for hour long patrols in the rain in Japan and all over the middle east and it has never hiccuped. And if it did I know from experience that Surefire's customer service is second to none. You will pay more for this light then an el cheapo from the local superstore but what you get is a good run time and utter reliability. It won't fall apart of fail you when you need it most, the only down point this light has is the bulb which like all bulbs burns out eventually. Surefire has remedied this with their new LED version though. You can't go wrong with this one.

B002NRQLBA.description: The Fenix remote pressure switch is specially designed for tactical flashlights. With four internal sensors< the switch activates your flashlight by applying slight finger pressure. Once pressure is released the switch turns the flashlight off. With its 80cm cable (Max length) for remote control of the flashlight, Fenix remote pressure switch makes your tactical mission or hunting trip more practical and convenient.  Fits models TK12, TA20, TA21
B002NRQLBA.title: Fenix Remote Switch (TK12, TA20, TA21)
B002NRQLBA.Best review: Well made, solid, my opinion?  They could have charged like $30 for the thing and I would have still bought it.  Really nice set up for an AR15.  An additional nice feature is end cap has its own on off button for continuious use, unlike others I have bought.  That's a really nice feature.

B000QWUQUQ.description: The dual-switch Smith & Wesson Galaxy 28 flashlight is designed with two separate on-off push buttons, providing a choice between a powerfully bright 20 White LED mode or two battery-efficient LED modes--4 red LED (for night vision) or 4 blue LED (for low light viewing)--without the confusion of a single switch mechanism. It features the latest MSAT switch technology which allows the white LEDs to operate on one switch while the color LED modes are activated on a separate switch. Ideal for aviation, outdoors, automotive, home, and professional use, the 20 LED mode provides a brilliant beam of white light perfect for general usage, while the 4 LED mode is ideal for conserving battery power and signaling and identifying targets at night without hampering night vision. It's constructed of precision-machined 6063 anodized aluminum for maximum resistance to corrosion and weather. The flashlight also includes 3 AAA batteries and a deluxe holster with a spare battery holder. It's backed by a limited lifetime warranty.
B000QWUQUQ.title: Smith & Wesson Galaxy 28 LED Flashlight (20 White, 4 Red & 4 Blue LEDs)
B000QWUQUQ.Best review: Here is one light that is BRIGHT!  Not only do you have 20 white LED, but 4 Red and 4 blue!  The white is for your general night viewing.  Red lights help keep your night vision.  Blue are for low light areas.  Personally I like the same light, but with the 4 green LED instead of the blue (do a search here at amazon as it's available).  But the I've found a good use for the blue in looking at maps at night.It comes with a great carrying case you can clip on your belt through a velcro backing.  And on the outside of the case is a small pocket to put three extra batteries.Those who work nights and need a good light (Law Enforcement, EMS), here is the light you need.  It looks stylish, and feels good in your hand.  Ends are squared so that it does not roll.  The middle of the light where you hold it are grooved so the light does not "sweat out" of your hands.Battery power is good.  Like any light it will not last 12 hours constantly on.  But the 20 white LED are bright yet seem to use less power.  And the red and blue use even less power and will work even when the white is dim or out as they use even less power.

B003F88740.description: Bright white LED delivers 30 lumens 3 light modes: Red night vision/ Low/ High. White low/high and Red Attaches above the brim of a cap so light does not block vision Swivels 90 degree to point light where it's needed Compact & lightweight.

B0018KS364.Best review: I have owned this headlamp for about 2 years and it's still going strong.  I bought it for its durability and warranty.  I use it quite often.  I have used the red LED a lot more than I imagined I would. Having the options of high - low - red and green are more useful than you might initially think.  Possibly my biggest pro is the fact it uses AA batteries instead of AAA's.  AA's have twice the energy capacity and are cheaper than AAA's.  I use rechargeables so my befefit is primarly run time.  As far as power goes, I rarely need the high setting.  70 lumens on high is plenty of power for looking out to 50+ yards.  You typically aren't searching that far with a headlamp.  The headlamps with the 200-300 lumen that use AAA's are IMO a waste.  IF you need that kind of power why would you power the tool with a low capacity AAA, your runtime would be horrible.  I give it 5 stars.  Versatile, dependadble, good run time, good power.Aug 2013: Still using this light.  The fabric straps are ugly now but the light continues to work great. I lost it for 3 months, at least I thought I did.  My daughter had scooped it but I have it back now.

B000FLESY8.description: A proven necessity for hurricane preparedness, the Garrity Power Lite lets you crank up the power with a few turns of the handle. B000FLESY8.title: Garrity Power Lite 3 LED Crank Light

B005OLIFZC.description: Features a CREE XP-G2 R5 LED (Cool White)Max Output: 349 LED lumen, 230 ANSI OTF lumenBeam Profile: Center lux: 2800lux; Center spot angle: 4.9°; Spill light angle: 33°Lens: Impact resistance waterwhite glass lens; Anti-scratch sapphire coating on the outside; Anti-reflective (AR) coating on the insideReflector: Very light orange peel aluminum reflectorHAIII hard anodization aerospace aluminumWaterproof: IPX-8 standardDimensions: Head Diameter: 0.78 inches (20 mm); Body Dia. 0.78 inches (20 mm); Length: 2.7 inch (69 mm; Weight: 0.99 ounces (28.2 grams)Battery Type: 1xCR123A; Compatible battery size (each): Diameter: 16-16.9mm, Length: 34-34.9mmWhat's included: Stainless steel bezel, Spare o-rings; Polished stainless steel pocket clip, User Manual, Rigid Nylon Holster w/ self-retention device and flip, Mil-Spec Paracord Lanyard w/ quick attachment clip
B005OLIFZC.title: EagleTac D25C Mini  XP-G2 LED Flashlight
B005OLIFZC.Best review: This is the first flashlight I have owned that uses the CR123 Battery.  The upside of these batteries is that they lend to a flashlight design that is very small and light weight, but still produces a lot of lumen output with respectable runtimes.  The downside of the CR123 is that it isn't as readily available as AA or AAA batteries, so you need to stock up ahead of time.I'm not sure why Eagle Tac is touting 325 "LED Lumens" (maybe some kind of marketing ploy), but "OTF Lumen" specs is what matters. Still the OTF output of 209 on High is excellent for this type of flashlight and there is a very useful 60 lumen Medium and 3 lumen Low mode. I really like the lower low like the Eagle Tac compared to the Fenix lights which run 7 - 10 Lumens in low.Runtimes on the Eagle Tac are comparable with other CR123 lights, but you have to respect the fact that you only have about 1 hour on the highest output, so for extended runtimes best to switch to 60 Lumen mode, which gives you 5 hours.  The light has a nice hot spot with generous amount of flood, but still throws a good distance.The extra strobe & flashing modes are very nice to have and real bonus on a light of this size especially at this price point. The included accessory package is also very generous and I really like the sturdy clip. A perfect EDC (Every Day Carry) light! Mine never leaves my pocket.

B003788U9U.description: The Bug is the smallest knife in innovative cutlery company Spyderco's product line. A razor sharp, go-anywhere slip-joint folder, the compact knife's flat-ground blade is made of stainless steel that holds a keen edge over time, and the handle is also made of satin-finished stainless steel. The end of the handle has a lanyard hole large enough to accept a small chain or key ring. Part of Spyderco's new SLIPITS line, the Bug features a non-locking, slip-joint design, with no locking mechanism holding the blade open. Instead, the blade is held open by resistant pressure at the pivot area when the blade is extended and being used.Specifications2.875-inch open length1.625-inch closed length1.3-inch 3Cr13 steel blade1.125-inch cutting edge0.19-inch blade hole0.06-inch blade thickness0.4-ounce weightWarrantySypderco knives include a limited manufacturer's warranty against defects in materials and workmanship. Details are included with your purchase.About SpydercoThinking beyond established knife industry practices has allowed Spyderco to introduce new innovations, including one-hand opening, serrations on a folder, and a clip to attach a knife to a pocket. Spyderco remains dedicated to researching and developing improved, better-performing materials with function and reliability, and its unique cutlery line is a result of designing ergonomic, functional tools. The company puts its new products through rigorous testing prior to release, examining edge retention with a CATRA machine, looking for rust development with Q-FOG, checking the force needed to open and close a knife, and analyzing numerous other technical details.
B003788U9U.title: Spyderco Bug SS Slip Joint Plain Edge Knife
B003788U9U.Best review: I'm a knife hound and when I saw some Spyderco's on Amazon's website for under $10, I had to take the plunge. The SLIPITs from smallest to largest (so far) are the Bug -> Honeybee -> Grasshopper. The Bug is easily the easiest to call "cute" - because that's exactly what it is. I've uploaded a couple of customer images comparing the three knives to each other (and next to my "real" Spyderco) so you can get an idea of how small these things really are.The only reason I've marked my Bug at 4 stars instead of 5 is the fact that it doesn't have a locking mechanism. Having worked with full-sized EDCs with and without locks, I can say that locks always come in handy, no matter what the size of the knife. While I don't plan on having to take down a wild boar with this knife, a simple locking mechanism would have been nice.That being said, I still love the little thing. It's small enough to go anywhere - even fitting inside some wallets (for women, this thing fits in nicely in the change pocket). I have it clipped to the little lanyard inside of my purse so I can have it with me almost all the time. Of course the concern would be accidentally taking this through the security check. Key chain knife?  Yeah it'd work - even though it doesn't have an open lock, the blade has quite a bit of friction keeping it closed, and since the blade isn't very heavy it doesn't try to "open itself". The blade is pretty thin, so I wouldn't use it to try and manhandle screws or pry open (whatever), but it holds a razor sharp edge.

B00BD50T2U.description: Taking inspiration from the classic "Trench Knives" from both World Wars of the last century, we have developed a tactical fixed blade that is suitable for today's modern day warriors. The unique "D" ring guard is made from reinforced 6061 aluminum allowing for an incredibly secure and comfortable grip while protecting the hand both from incoming attack and damage while striking or cutting an opponent who's covered in body armor, ammo, flashlights, magazines and gear! The thick 1055 carbon steel pommel is tapered for ferocious Punyo or Butt-Strikes and the 7 1/2" SK-5 high carbon blade is available in either Double Edge or Tanto blade shapes. Additionally, the Chaos series is coated in black Tuff-Ex, aiding corrosion resistance and enhancing cutting power by reducing friction. They come complete with a tough Secure-Ex sheath, which features a belt loop for dependable, versatile carry. Specifications: Blade Length: 7 1/2"; Overall Length: 13 1/2"; Steel: SK-5 High Carbon; Weight: 17 oz. (Approx.); Blade Thickness: 4.5 mm; Handle: 6" Long, 6061 Aluminum; Sheath: Secure-Ex Sheath.
B00BD50T2U.title: Cold Steel 80NTP Chaos Double Edge Knife
B00BD50T2U.Best review: What an impressive knife to hold in your hand!  This is a modern version of the WWI  knuckle buster used in hand-to-hand combat in the trenches when firearms weren't available or were unusable in tight quarters. You could stab, slash, punch and strike with it to great effect.  If you want to have some fun, buy a watermelon or pumpkin and go for it. You will find it best used to stab and strike (with the pommel).  Slashing to bare skin would be effective, but not on a target with layers of clothing. To be an effective slasher, you would need something larger and heavier like the Busse Argonne Assault--which costs 10 times as much.I found it to fit my hand perfectly, both with and without gloves.  The fit is critical if you use the knuckle guard to punch.  A poor fit will result in it turning in your hand and quickly make you understand why it was called a "knuckle buster".  The blade came very sharp and well oiled and there was no play in the blade or handle.  The Secure-Ex sheath fits the knife perfectly and allows it to be carried in different configurations.  There is some evidence that constantly drawing the knife from this sheath will dull the blade over time, so be sure to draw it straight out of the sheath.Good solid construction for a very reasonable price. Make sure that you display it in your collection.  The industrial Steampunk design will draw a lot of eyes to it. Everyone will wonder where you got that cool looking knife.

B004I2EMXM.description: Tough as nails and powerful enough to produce a beam of light up to 577 feet ahead of you, the Fenix TK35 flashlight is the perfect choice for camping, backpacking, or simply lighting up the night. A single push-button cycles this flashlight through three different modes, and the built-in memory circuit starts this flashlight at the brightness level you were using when you shut it off. Fenix paid close attention to the details of construction and design, and it even made this pocket-sized light waterproof up to two meters.
B004I2EMXM.title: Fenix TK35 Flashlight
B004I2EMXM.Best review: I recently purchased the TK35 and was disappointed with the performance when using 18650 batteries. It was quite a bit brighter with 4 CR123 batteries. But then it was suggested to me that even though I purchased a reasonably good quality pair of Trustfire True 2400mah 18650 batteries, that maybe they just didn't have enough power for the turbo mode. So I spent $32 on a pair of really good quality Panasonic 3100mah 18650 batteries from Callies Kustoms and I am so blown away by the difference! The TK35 now gets just as bright as with the CR123 batteries, and they last WAY WAY longer!! NO CONTEST!!!The TK35 ran down the four $16 energizer CR123s in just over 90 mins (not all at one time) to where there was no more turbo mode available. But these Panasonic 18650s went for over 3 hours on turbo (again not all at one time). I ride about 1 hour every night, and pretty much run the light on turbo the whole time. I always give it a couple minutes rest on regular high every ten minutes or so, then right back up to turbo, and they're rechargable!! So cool!! I just wanted anyone out there who ran into this same problem to know that all 18650s are definitely not equal, and an investment in a good pair of Panasonic 18650s will ultimately save you money in the long run, and will allow your light to work at the brightness it was designed to operate. And let's face it, if you spent approx. $100 bucks for a top quality flashlight like the TK35, you want it to get as bright as it's supposed to!! (Ideally without having to spend $20 dollars a week on batteries!)

B0019Z9AJM.description: The Energizer Weatheready Compact 2 LED Flashlight will give you the light needed in tight places. Operating on 4AA Energizer Max batteries deliver an impressive 77 hours of run time and 19 lumens of light output.  The non-slip rubber grip ensures secure handling.
B0019Z9AJM.title: Energizer Weather Ready Compact 2 LED Flashlight
B0019Z9AJM.Best review: Nice tight beam, about 6 feet circular and pretty bright on a wall from 20 feet away. Not a lot of peripheral light but a solid beam. This is the type of flashlight you would want (or I would) going into a garage/basement when the power goes out or if going outside to check a fuse box. Nice feel in the hand. Good to have on hand, in a drawer etc. Switch feels a little soft, no "click" in either position but I would buy it again............*************************Update, the switch started "clicking" with some use. Don`t know if that is good or bad. Simple design though, if switch goes you can easily "rebuild" it. I still would buy another one...........

B000QWUQDI.description: The Smith & Wesson Galaxy 9 LED Flashlight is a great light to use around the house or in the car. Nine White LEDs illuminate a large area in low light environments. It also works very well in professional settings when a general illumination is needed, such as electronics and car repair. The Limited Lifetime Warranty guarantees the quality and reliability you have come to expect from Smith & Wesson since 1852.
B000QWUQDI.title: Smith & Wesson Galaxy 9 LED Flashlight (9 White LEDS)
B000QWUQDI.Best review: If you have never used a modern LED flashlight before, you might be impressed by the progress made in the flashlight industry when you use this.This flashlight uses 3 AAA batteries stacked to get enough voltage for the white LEDs.  That's an OK method to make a very low-cost flashlight with moderate light output and longer runtime than an old bulb flashlight.  The drawback is light which begins to drop almost immediately, but it remains usable for a long time.But this thing is priced about 3 times what it is sold for when when not branded.  You can get the same thing in a generic form for MUCH less.For the price of this Smith/Wesson, you can go the next step up get any of several brands of flashlights which use a single AA battery with a voltage regulator and produces more light.  The light output typically remains constant for longer as well.I would either get this similar flashlight for a lot less:Super-Bright 9 LEDOr this Inova X1 (similar brightness, more focused, smaller size) for the same price:Inova X1MT-WB X1 AA-Battery Powered FlashlightOr get a "Life Gear" 1-AA flashlight at Target (thanks to whomever suggested this as a reply to another of my reviews), which is both brighter and better-focused.EDIT: I don't know why I did not originally include the Microstream as another alternative.  It is a nice slim little flashlight, almost keychain-size, with a similar price and performance to the latest Inova X1:Streamlight 66318 MicroStream LED Pen Flashlight

B0018KOJSK.description: The Energizer Ultimate Lithium Light features a powerful CREE LED that provides 110 lumens of bright, white light in a compact, durable design. Push button tail-switch regulates brightness with the touch of a finger. Constructed of machined aircraft aluminum casing and has a runtime of 3.5 hours of maximum light output when powered by Energizer Ultimate Lithium 2AA batteries. Features a automatic 30 minute shutoff if accidently activated. Compact, waterproof, rugged design with shatterpoff lens and lifetime gaurantee.
B0018KOJSK.title: Energizer Ultimate Lithium Flashlight
B0018KOJSK.Best review: I love flashlights, so when I saw it in my local store I just had to get it. I've had this flashlight for about 2 years now, but I paid 2x of what it costs now :(Intensity of the beam is incredible (110 lumen), this is the brightest light I had so far.Besides carrying it with me, I found a great use for it as a light for my commuter bike. I got a $2 generic rubber light holder on ebay which you can attach to handlebar and this flashlight fits nicely. My commute is short so I never had problems with 30min shutoff, and it lights my way just great be it in total darkness or twilight. Makes me feel safe.There are "better" bike lights, but they require external batter pack and cost 10x more. Why bother, for my needs I go thru just 1 set of lithium batters a year, they seem to last long.Lithium batteries are expensive (but you can use alkaline or rechargeable), true, but they are also very light and great for carrying on hikes/camping. I even took it with me on my Hawaii trip. I went into a totally dark lava tube, and there were some people there with headlights. When I turned my Energizer, it cut thru the darkness like a projector, someone event screamed "ok you win!", we all had a good laugh :)Someone here mentioned about light flickering, I never had this issue. Output is steady, and you can regulate it's intensity by holding on/off button. Also it doesn't scratch easily. I carry it with me in my bag full of junk and didn't notice any damage so far.

B00008BFS8.description: The Streamlight Propolymer Xenon Flashlight was truly built to last! This handheld flashlight features a high density super tough nylon construction with a rubber face cap. Its waterproof and shock resistant making it the perfect companion on any of your outdoor adventures! The Propolymer flashlight features 7 bright LED lights (available in blue or white) and a tail switch for momentary blink or constant on settings. A wrist lanyard a 4 AA batteries are included.
B00008BFS8.title: Streamlight ProPolymer 4 AA LED Flashlight
B00008BFS8.Best review: I have become a huge fan of this light.  I used to only use the SureFire and Streamlight "Lithium Battery" type lights, but after a hundred dollars worth of replacement batteries I thought I should find something that doesnt take $15-$20 worth of batteries at a shot. I then found a major disapointment in the LED/Regular bulb selectable setup of another Streamlight I purchased.  My next option was this one, I am completely satasfied and now have two for around the house and one for my wifes car and another for my car.  These are small, sturdy, easy to manipulate, have a long battery life and give out a fantastic amount of light.As the actual light goes, it is very crisp and bluish white colored.  It lights up a large area nicely.  It does not travel a long distace but easily provides enough light to light up a room or trail, or to work on a car at night.Another great thing about this light, funny as it sounds, is that the handle is not round, it is oblong shaped.  Sounds odd until you have to hold it in your mouth while using both your hands to change a tire on your car, then you understand how handly that handle really is.This is a great light, bright, compact, inexpensive, long battery life.  Almost everything you could ask for in a light for around the house or to keep in the car.

B005I5ML36.description: These MREs are genuine U.S. military issue. Each contains a full 12 meals, and every meal includes a flameless ration heater--all you need is water and a few minutes to have a hot meal. Each comes sealed in a waterproof airtight polymer bag, and includes an entree, side dish, crackers/bread, spread, dessert/candy, and a cold beverage base. They also feature amenities like utensils, napkins, matches, creamer, sugar, salt, and gum. Some have hot beverages or hot sauce, depending on the meal. Each meal provides around 1200 calories for an active person on the move, and is tailored to provide a good mix of protein, fat, and carbs (13/36/51&#37;) for optimum nutrition.Whether camping, hiking, hunting, traveling, or simply staying prepared for emergencies, MREs offer a simple, easy-to-store, easy-to-transport package that can mean a hot, nutritional, and filling meal whenever or wherever you need.
B005I5ML36.title: MREs (Meals Ready-to-Eat) Box B, Genuine U.S. Military Surplus, Menus 13-24
B005I5ML36.Best review: We're slowly trying sampling these MREs. I do not know the date code for this product and wonder how old it is.

B005O0RSTM.description: The Nite Ize BugLit LED Task Light is a unique combination of their powerful INOVA Microlight and securely attached flexible, grippy "legs" ( 6-inch Nite Ize Gear Ties) which can be attached or stored nearly anywhere!. The cleaver bug design's legs fold neatly around its body for compact attachment to zippers or keys. Attach to your pack with its lightweight plastic S-Biner or wrap it around your bike's handlebars, basket, frame, bike rack or seat post. This tough, micro LED flashlight puts an innovative twist on bicycle safety with its universally recognized white (for front) and red (for rear) lights, to keep your bike safely seen by other commuters when you're out riding in the dark. The BugLit - LED Task Light body is encased in a durable polycarbonate plastic housing, with four functions (high power, low power, strobe, and signal). The bright LED has an effective range of up to 50 feet, and one-mile visibility.Strong internal wire that holds its shape..Quick and easy to securely attach and detach..UV resistant - will not be damaged by extended sun exposure..Size #0 S-Biner is a durable, lightweight double gated carabiner clip - attach or store nearly anywhere!.Water Resistant: IPX4.Battery: Two CR2016.
B005O0RSTM.title: Nite Ize Buglit LED Task Light
B005O0RSTM.Best review: Pretty simple product, great idea. We own a few of these and have given some as stocking-stuffers. They are surprisingly bright for something so tiny, and the 'arms' and 'legs' bend easily yet hold firmly to the tops of books (think book light), to a rear-view mirror, and so on. The uses are only bound by your imagination (and its about 10-foot working distance).Fun product.Update 2012-dec-10: I accidentally got to test the IPX rating via a brief dunk in the sink. Seems fine. In case you're wondering what the IPX ratings actually say:IPX 4  Protected against splashing water. Same as level 3 but water is sprayed at all angles.and 3 (since it's the basis for 4) says:IPX 3  Protected against spraying water.  Water spraying up to 60 degrees from vertical at 10 liters/min at a gage pressure of 80-100kN/m2 for 5 min.

B0090UW9E6.description: Mora Craftline series feature sharp, durable utility knives suitable for construction, trade and industrial professionals. Mora Knives are made from high-quality Sandvik steel. Sandvik knife steels are characterized by ultra-fine carbides that result in superb forging and hardening properties. The absence of large carbide deposits promotes excellent edge sharpness for optimum cutting performance. Morakniv has been manufacturing the highest-quality knives in Mora, Sweden since 1891. Professionals worldwide trust the quality materials and fine craftsmanship of Mora Knives. Mora knives feature ergonomically-designed handles and employ premium-quality knife steel that is optimally adapted to the task for which the knife is intended.
B0090UW9E6.title: Morakniv Craftline Q Allround Fixed Blade Utility Knife with Sandvik Stainless Steel Blade, 3.8-Inch
B0090UW9E6.Best review: I really like Mora knives and these one is stainless they offer the red one in carbon steel but if you don't like patinas or are not very good at taking care of your knives this one will work great. Nice light weight with a functional sheath very sharp and easy to sharpen, the retention on the sheath is not that great, it is not horrible but you might want to secure it with a piece of cord around the handle and belt loop just in case. Mora offers many different knives and styles most high carbon have red handle and stainless blue handle, there are some other models that don't follow these color scheme, like the outdoorsman 2000(green or orange both stainless), the HighQ robust, companion HD, etc. This is a knife that can't be beat for the price.

B003W5X22S.description: A high-efficiency LED and deep reflector create a smooth beam on either low or high. A sleek pen-shaped aluminum body is durable easy to carry and features a sturdy pocket clip that keeps Solo securely in place. Because losing a flashlight this stylish and functional is not something you'll get over easily.Features: High-strength aluminum body with sturdy pocket clip Durable power-regulated LED maximizes output and runtime; never needs replacing Micro-textured reflector creates a smooth powerful beam Ergonomic "clickie" tailcap switch allows for easy switching between two output levels Sealed with O-rings; weatherproof Powered by two AAA alkaline batteries; includedSpecs: Light output: 16/2 lumens Runtime: 3/75 hours Length: 5.5 inches Weight: 2.2 ounces Battery: Two AAA alkalines Product : ICON SOLO PEN LIGHT 2-AAA GRAY Manufacturer : ICON Manufacturer Part No : SL102A UPC : 084871314756
B003W5X22S.title: Icon Solo Flashlight (Titanium )
B003W5X22S.Best review: This is my go to light all day every day and I recommend it to other nurses I work with.  It's VERY sturdy, gives me two light settings, clips to my shirt or sits in my pocket and hasn't failed me yet.  The light is either really bright or soft which works perfect for my mixed needs on the floor.  You have to push on and off to cycle between to the two settings which took a little getting used to but I don't even notice anymore, I just click what I need to click when I need the bright or dim.  The battery life is great, I've had one for over a year and still haven't changed it yet.  I ordered another two more because they were hard to find and I want to make sure if and when I need a replacement I've got one close at hand.  My husband thinks it looks cool so if that's a deciding factor take it for what it is.  I just think it's a functional fit for my needs.

B002JUDJBG.description: The Cashstash Capsule/keychain from True Utility provides and elegant and secure way to carry emergency cash on your keychain. B002JUDJBG.title: True Utility Cashstash Cash Capsule

Its large enough for some big pills, mine are not, and seals up tighter without leaking.  I bought several of the cheaper ones and one of the smaller ones just to have a selection, this one is by far the best.  I mean BY FAR the best.

B0028NEWD8.description: The Escort safety glass line with accompany you to any task you encounter. With matching side lenses and durable shatterproof lenses, the Escort will fit over most prescription eyewear. The Escort line meets the ANSI Z87.1-2003 Standards for use in industrial applications.
B0028NEWD8.title: Global Vision Eyewear Escort Safety Glasses, Smoke Tint Lens
B0028NEWD8.Best review: these are the best I was able to find for the price. recently found out that I have glaucoma and have to wear sun glasses forever

B001F0M2U0.description: The Ultra-Light Sound Sensor hearing protection device, from firearm supplier Allen Company, is a compact, convenient set that consistently outperforms electronic protection and allows easy conversation without the irritating "echo" effect. Noise reduction rated to 26 NRR and weighing just 1.7 ounces, the device additionally features a patented, adjustable headband that folds down to 2.5 by 5.75 inches (W x H) to fit easily into your pocket. Soft foam ear cushions are quite comfortable, and an extra pair is included with your purchase.Comfortable, noise-dampening foam cushions are easy on your ears, and a patented headband means you can stow the earplugs in your pocket.About Allen CompanyHeadquartered in Broomfield, Colorado, The Allen Company was founded in 1972 and is a leading supplier of gun cases, hunting accessories, and outdoor products.
B001F0M2U0.title: Allen Company Light Weight Low Profile Sound Sensor Hearing Protection, 2320
B001F0M2U0.Best review: I got these as a gift and have used both over the ear and inside the ear protection.  These were very uncomfortable. I tried all the foam plugs, but it still felt weird in the ears.  The part that goes up the sides is essentially an open tube that muffles the sound. The problem is that as you move around it acts as an amplifier to the scratchy sound it makes as it rubs on your hat, hair, head.  Like wearing a stethoscope.  You can't hear people talking around you, but any touching on the unit creates dull scratching noises.  I tossed them out.

B001H4I7GM.description: The Fenix PD20 is a high-tech, rugged tool that is perfect for any lighting application. It features six levels of output, which not only allows the user to select the best compromise between brightness and runtime for any given task, but also has ability to aid in an emergency. This small but mighty light features the following output levels: dim, regular, high, turbo, SOS and strobe. On the low output level, the PD20 can provide an amazing 35 hrs of use on one battery. The PD20 does all this and still retains an incredibly compact size. If you're looking for solid reliability, digitally regulated brightness, and compact size, this Fenix is for you.       • Cree Premium (Q5) 7090 XR-E LED with lifespan of 50,000 hours • 2 modes with 6 types of output • General Mode: 9 lumens (35hrs) -> 47 lumens (6.5hrs) -> 94 lumens (2.6hrs) ->SOS • Turbo Mode: 180 lumens (1hrs) -> Strobe • Digitally regulated output-maintains constant brightness • Uses one 3V CR123A battery (Lithium) • 83mm (Length) x 21.5mm (Diameter) • Made of T6 aircraft-grade aluminum • Durable Type III hard-anodized anti-abrasive finish • 39-gram weight (excluding batteries) • Waterproof to IPX-8 Standard • Toughened ultra-clear glass lens with anti-reflective coating • Push-button tail cap switch • Capable of standing up securely on a flat surface to serve as a candle • Included accessories: holster, lanyard, two spare o-rings, and a rubber switch boot
B001H4I7GM.title: Fenix PD20 CREE Q5 Mini LED Flashlight, Black, 180 Lumens, Uses 1 X CR123A Battery
B001H4I7GM.Best review: When I opened this product, I was shocked at the size.  I know the dimensions say how small it is, but you don't realize that your thumb might be bigger than it.  This out shined my other "best" flashlights that I have had for years.  My 3C cell, 3 pound, 12" long mag-light doesn't give 1/4 of the beam that this little Fenix gives.  When I received the item, I immediately ran a full sink of water, turned the flashlight on, dropped it from about 3 feet up into the water, and left it there while I fixed my dinner (bout 20 mins).  The Flashlight is proven waterproof, shockproof, and the batteries are very comparable to the price of 3C batteries.  I cannot imagine a more appropriate concealed super-flashlight.  The modes are fun to play with and are easy to switch.Other LED flashlights 5x the size and twice the cost can't match the output and efficiency of this little Fenix.  The pouch it comes in is highly dynamic for carry options.  I attach it to my belt next to my cell phone.  It is thin and light enough to never notice.  The beam, the modes, the button, the look, the size, and the included holster are exactly as they should be.  +5 stars for an outstanding product.

B005X1YIL8.description: 26-310-5-1 (blister pack) Five essential survival tools in durable hard plastic case: Compass Whistle Waterproof match box Fire starter flint & Signal Mirror Pocket-sized to fit anywhere Dimensions: 4.5 x 1.25 x 1.25 Weight: 1.2 oz.
B005X1YIL8.title: 5 in 1 Survival Tool

B0002THWDC.description: Bright LED with head band.  Free up your hands for kayaking, cycling, or even repair work.  Can switch between  2, 4, or 8 light.

Three brightness settings provide white light with forward, upward and downward positions. Positions hold well; adjustment feels calibrated. The product isn't weighty and generally durable.I'm glad I got it. Can't think of anything wrong with it. Uses three triple A's.

B003C841BQ.description: The Nebo CSI EDGE 35 is a compact high-intensity tactical LED flashlight. With an anodized aircraft grade aluminum construction; The EDGE outputs 35 lumens. The water-resistant body design also features a steel clip to keep this flashlight handy!
B003C841BQ.title: Nebo CSI Edge Flashlight, Assorted Colors
B003C841BQ.Best review: I purchased mine from a bicycle shop. It worked great for about 3 months. Then the led started strobing. Sent it back to Nebo Tools and they sent me a new one that died in a matter of minutes. Sent that back and they sent me one with the head and barrel cross threaded. Sent that back and they sent me one with a bad switch. The cost of sending the flashlights back has now exceeded the  cost of the original flashlight. I will not send the last flashlight back. I will keep it to remind me to never buy from a company that does not take pride in their products. Oh, and by the way, a flashlight that doesn't work when you need it is a dangerous tool to have around.

B004D2A02O.description: Smaller doesn’t mean weaker with this durable, long-reaching flashlight. E05 takes compact on the road with reliable Fenix performance under extreme conditions.
B004D2A02O.title: Fenix Flashlight
B004D2A02O.Best review: Even thought this light output reads 27 Lumens, the lens works like a flood light and provides massive short range light.  Inside 25 feet, this single AAA flashlight outshines my old 3xC cell Maglight for rich penetrating beam.  After 25-30', the beam diffuses too much to be much use.  The 2 pound-14 inch Maglight will shine about 50-60' with decent but uneven lighting distribution, but this Fenix E05 R2 is smaller than my car key fob, waterproof (tested), shockproof and inexpensive!  It is small and light enough to be tucked behind an ear like a pencil.The CR123 battery flashlights are much thicker and often more expensive to use.  Plus I got sick of changing the "modes" on my flashlight so the kids didn't burn up the battery in an hour.  This twist cap takes a very deliberate action and likely will not activate in your pocket.  Btw, a small piece of hollowed out 550 paracord makes a sturdy and attractive lanyard for this flashlight because it does not come with a lanyard or battery.  Both completely understandable for such a high quality and high value item.  5 stars with a bullet.

It comes in a sealed package with our trademarked logo and header card.*
B008DMSPOK.title: Type-III Apocalypse Pry Bar with 7 Strand 550 Paracord Wrapped Handle and Mini Compass
B008DMSPOK.Best review: Let me start by saying, this will become a trend in must have items for a small, sturdy, Bug-Out-Baggable prybar. The addition of many colors of Paracord and a small compass makes this an unbeatable deal. Will be ordering more and recommending to my friends and fellow preppers. Great product, try it you'll love it from first use.

B007VKUQW4.description: Convenient carabiner clips to bags, packs, purses, etc. Pushbutton switch glows in the dark. Reflective surface on head for safety Features side-lighting lens. Water resistant construction.
B007VKUQW4.title: Energizer Weatheready Compact 3-LED Safety Flashlight (Battery Included)

B003XP9IBQ.description: The Fenix 4 pack accessory kit includes the following:  Red Filter Adapter, Diffuser Lens, Diffuser Tip (white cone), and Traffic Wand (orange cone).
B003XP9IBQ.title: Fenix Accessory Kit - LD and PD Series (4 Piece Kit)
B003XP9IBQ.Best review: Good design all around.  The traffic safey cone and cone diffuser are pretty good.  Hoever the major drawbacks to this product is the quality of the plastic.  It is too brittle.  Because it is so brittle it will crack and you do not get a good seal at the rear of the filters.  Especially for the red filer.  There is alot of white light spash back at the rear of it.

B00EARSTZW.description: The NEW Olight S10-L2 is part of the innovative Baton series, known for tough lights that are barely larger than the batteries that power them.  The S10-L2 combines a side switch and great output (400 lumens on high) into a very compact size.  The S10-L2 has four outputs, including a super low moonlight mode that can be accessed from off, meaning that you don't have to cycle through a bunch of night vision ruining modes in the pitch black of the night.  A magnet is integrated into the tailcap, allowing you to attach the light to a ferrous surface.
B00EARSTZW.title: Olight S10-L2 Baton 400 Lumen LED Flashlight EDC
B00EARSTZW.Best review: My favorite of ~10 small lights I own. Great beam. Sharp cone of light. Really bright. With most lights of this type, using the RCR123 3.7v rechargeable lithiums can almost double light output. The S-10 gives you 350 lumens of light with CR123's and only 430 with the RCR123's. (That's good. It's already really bright using the CR123 primary batteries.) You should go to Candle Power Forums, on the web, and read Selfbuilt's flashlight reviews.

B00816PZ8W.description: Mora Craftline Series include sharp, durable, high-quality utility knives suitable for construction, trade and industrial professionals. The High Q Robust knife is an all around craft knife with carbon steel blade and extra-large grip. Grey plastic Combo-Sheath gives you the ability to connect your favorite knives. Craftline HighQ knives feature ergonomic double-molded handles with a high friction grip. Mora knives made from High Carbon Steel achieve high hardness, sharpen easily and are exceptionally tough. High carbon steels are preferred in applications that demand durability and frequent regrinding. The material is harder than stainless steel, allowing it to hold a sharper and more durably acute edge. Mora Knives are made from high-quality Sandvik steel. Sandvik knife steels are characterized by ultra-fine carbides that result in superb forging and hardening properties. The absence of large carbide deposits promotes excellent edge sharpness for optimum cutting performance. Morakniv has been manufacturing the highest-quality knives in Mora, Sweden since 1891. Professionals worldwide trust the quality materials and fine craftsmanship of Mora Knives. Mora knives feature ergonomically-designed handles and employ premium-quality knife steel that is optimally adapted to the task for which the knife is intended.
B00816PZ8W.title: Morakniv Craftline HighQ Robust Trade Knife with Sandvik Carbon Steel Blade and Combi-Sheath, 4.1-Inch
B00816PZ8W.Best review: The blade is basically just a thicker version of the companion and also has a deeper handle.  The thicker blade means that it won't slice as well, but it's tougher.  The handle would fit people with large hands well but is too wide for small hands and is not as comfortable as the companion in an average sized hand.

B008HU8P52.description: Whether you're under the hood working on your car or starting up the trail for a weekend camping excursion, the full-featured Fenix HL30 Headlamp provides the powerful hands-free lighting you need for the job. With a maximum 200 lumen output, the HL30 can cast a beam 131 feet into the darkness and the Broad Beam System completely illuminates the immediate area. A total of six settings gives you options for every lighting situation and the water-resistant protection prevents you from being stranded in the dark when a rain shower rolls through.
B008HU8P52.title: Fenix HL30 Headlamp
B008HU8P52.Best review: This thing continues to astonish me when I turn it on, especially in comparison to my old headlamp.  The great thing is that it has several settings so you can dim the light for general camp use (to save battery) then turn it full blast if you need to do some night hiking.  It also has a red light mode which is great when you get up in the middle of the night and do not want to wake up your tent mates with a bright light.I liked it so much I immediately bought a second one for my girlfriend.  Maybe now she'll stop asking to borrow mine....

B003TFOPJA.description: Get a two pack of the top rated / best selling bicycle hoist on the market! There is no such thing as not enough room for another bike. Store your bikes overhead and out of the way. Smooth pulleys and latches make lifting even heavy bikes super easy. The exclusive rope locking mechanism prevents unwanted release and can suspend one bike - 100 lb. load limit. Please note, you can mount this item as pictured or on a 2 x 4 and then onto the ceiling. RAD Cycle Products is an industry leader and backs it up with a warranty which is the best in the business!
B003TFOPJA.title: RAD Cycle Products Bike Lift Hoist Garage Mountain Bicycle Hoist 100LB Capacity (2-Pack)
B003TFOPJA.Best review: We bought this to help keep our bikes out of the way of our cars.The unit works well, but I think it would be better for garages with higher roofs then ours has.  Still, it is a good choice, especially at such a low price.  It does the job well, and installation was easy.

B000FOW0Q8.description: Optronics Waterproof LED 6 and 7 Function Trailer Light Kit. Has all the components necessary to bring a trailer up to DOT lighting requirements for both under and over 80in applications. Full 3-year warranty. Specific DOT installation instructions. Trilingual packaging and instructions (English, French, Spanish). 1-800 Technical assistance hot-line number.2 LED stud-mount tail lights, red side marker/reflectors, license bracket, 25 Feet wiring harness and hardware. Life time manufacturer. warranty. Clam packed.
B000FOW0Q8.title: Optronics (TLL-9RK) LED Sealed Trailer Light Kit
B000FOW0Q8.Best review: I love these lights. I have bought 4 sets now and will keep buying them until i learn how to drive and stop smashing them.My flatbed trailer has a really annoyingly low mount for the lights and will get taken out if backed over a curb or even when pulling out of a steep driveway to road transition. I actually keep a spare set in my truck when i tow the trailer because i drove back from LA with no lights on one occasion. Not a gripe about the lights in any way, just the location on my trailer that smashes them between the frame and the ground. I even lost a light over a speed bump once. I need to re-weld the light mounts in a better location...Anyways, enough bitching about my flatbed trailer.The lights are super bright and are LED so they draw nearly no load. The left light has a license plate light to keep you in compliance with the law if you mount your plate under the light. I dont, but that's my problem.I cant really comment about their long term lifespan, the longest i have had a set is 2 years now before i broke the mounting bolts out the back. The light still worked perfectly, it was just dangling by the wires.I should also note that the current set on my flatbed are directly in the spray of the tires and both housings are broken and exposed. I expected them to stop working the first rainstorm i drove through, but that was about a year ago and they are still working perfectly.So all in all, i love these lights. Just dont rest a 4000 lb trailer on them and expect them not to break.

B008XH3QAI.description: This LED light bulb is great in track lighting, canister and recessed fixtures.SpecificationsBulb Type: LED PAR20 with standard screw base (E26)Input Voltage: 120VAC, 60HzPower: 7.5WBeam Angle: 120Available Color Temperatures: White (5000-6500K) | Warm White (3000-3400K)Light Output (lumen): 370 | 320Product Diameter: 2.5"Product Length: 3.3"
B008XH3QAI.title: LEDwholesalers Dimmable PAR20 7.5 Watt E26 Screw Base LED Light Bulb Wide Angle for Recessed or Track Lights, 1330
B008XH3QAI.Best review: Needed something to replace 50 watt halogens in stove range hood.  These are perfect, they fit same as the old lights and are very bright with a good wide cast.  There is no change in output on low switch setting so I had to give up the dimming, but with no heat and less than 1/5 the electricity usage these are great.

B00I8YOUOC.description:
The Adventurer Survival Kit Box, part of the Best Glide Adventurer Series of Survival Equipment, is ideal for all of your outdoor needs. Because it is made of heavy duty aluminum with a leak resistant inside rubber seal and positive locking roller clasps, your items will stay clean and dry, even in extremely harsh conditions. 

Since the Adventurer Survival Kit Box is food safe, use it to store just about anything. This Adventurer Survival Kit Box is perfectly suited to store your lunch, fishing gear, hunting gear, photos, first aid kit, camera, wallet, valuables and of course, your survival equipment.
B00I8YOUOC.title: Adventurer Aluminum Survival Kit Box
B00I8YOUOC.Best review: Big vs. small- Survival tin size depends on you! I have included shots of my Every Day Carry- BCB tin, self stocked!, for comparison. I like this tin, the size is great for a pack or car. First what I don't like- not a big fan of anodized anything, it's like the egg thing- first it's good then bad, would not want to boil my water in it. The BCB tin wins in this area as it is just plain old aluminum. Second I have to agree that the rollers are not the greatest and their rubber so melting is an issue. I have no issue with the inner lid seal as you can see in the photo, it fits pretty well and is not all messed up.  It also has a sticker on bottom of it from the Adventurer series survival equipment on it, so guess you'll have to burn it off if you don't want it!This fits a LOT of items in it depending on your idea of survival gear, still filling mine! I don't really worry about it breaking open if I drop it, probably more that I'll dent it. The more gear you pack in them the more durable they are. The lid fits pretty snugly and the metal reminds me of the Coleman cooking pots, ya know the ones from Wally world. A little on the thin side, probably for weight control. Check out the photo's hope they give you a clearer picture!Bottom line: I like both my tins for different reasons, but either way you can't go wrong, happy with both purchases!

B000W9Q0GC.description: The New Wave Enviro 10-stage Premium Water Filter System produces a continuous supply of fresh, crisp, wonderful-tasting water right from your tap, removing major contaminants to below EPA minimum levels. The deceptively simple device quickly attaches to your faucet, and conversion kits are available to mount under your sink. An easily replaced filter produces approximately 1,500 gallons of water before it needs replacing -- enough to last a family of four for around a year.The filter removes or greatly reduces chlorine, carcinogenic organic and chlorine compounds called trihalomethanes (THM), bad odors such as hydrogen sulfide, pesticides, herbicides, PCBs, toxic heavy metals like lead, cadmium, organic arsenic, asbestos, micro-organisms such as cryptosporidium and giardia, and dozens of other organic contaminants. Once your water has been filtered, inert and desirable minerals like magnesium, potassium, chlorides, and fluoride are left behind.Guarantee and WarrantyNew Wave Enviro products include a 30-day unconditional money-back guarantee, as well as a limited one-year manufacturer's warranty against defects in materials and workmanship.About New Wave EnviroNew Wave Enviro was established in 1994 with a focus on providing pure, on-demand water at a reasonable price. The company manufactures and distributes products, which produce quality, inexpensive purified water from your own tap. In addition to filtration systems, New Wave Enviro additionally manufacture a complete line of reusable stainless steel, Eastar resin, and corn resin water bottles, ranging in size from eight ounces to five gallons.
B000W9Q0GC.title: New Wave Enviro 10 Stage Water Filter System
B000W9Q0GC.Best review: I used several technologies to clean tap water - reverse osmosis, distilled water, double filtration etc. This filter will not give you the purity of RV unit or distillation, but you are getting close to that quality without paying hundreds of dollars for better systems. Good buy at less then $100

B002MFK7BS.description: Compact and ready to go, this light never needs batteries. Cranking restores the rechargeable NiMH batteries to their charged state. The Nichia LEDs are bright, virtually unbreakable and never need replacing. Also, the light features a quick to use carabiner clip and the crank operates in either direction. Highly efficient use of Kinetic energy with 1 minute of cranking providing 3 minutes of light. This light is an excellent solution for extended power outages and situations where the light will be stored for a long period of time.
B002MFK7BS.title: Energizer Weatheready 3-LED Carabineer Rechargeable Crank Light, Red
B002MFK7BS.Best review: This is not an expert review, I've never owned nor used a crank light before.  I'm not a cave diver, mountain climber of any other kind of sport enthusiast who would know the ins and outs of the different kinds of equipment used for lighting.  I just know that this flashlight produces a nice amount of light, enough to light up the sidewalk after dark thereby illuminating any doggy turds left behind (I seem to possess an uncanny knack for finding the slimy piles with my clean and colorful sneakers).The crank is easy to use and sturdy enough that I don't worry that in my enthusiasm I might snap it off.The light is small enough to clip onto a shoulder bag or off of a belt for easy travel.The light has a nice sized grip handle and is pretty lightweight so that an hour's walk after dark doesn't leave you feeling that you need to work on increasing your upper body strength.Last of all, it's fun to use.  There's something kinda cool about winding the crank on this for light.  I usually hand it off to my son and he's always a little over zealous in the winding, but like I said before, this is a pretty durable light.

B00H6YIZKK.description:
CONTENTS - In The Friendly Swede retail packaging:1 x Carabiner "grenade" survival kit pull with eye knife, needle, wire, alcohol pad, tin foil, tinder, fire starter, fishing lines, fishing hooks, weights, swivels, dobber wrapped in 500 lb paracordSurivival kitOpen in case of emergency for a handful of essential tools that are hardest to improvise in the wild9 feet paracord to  tie, pull apart, improviseFire starter & Tinder to ignite fast and burn hotEye knife for cutting job2 fishing lines(5 meters), 2 weights, 2 swivels, 2 floats, 2 fishing hooks: where there's water, there's foodTin foil for signaling, cooking, reflecting heatNeedle for small repairs or suturesWire(2 meters) for trapping, snaring, bindingAlcohol pad for disinfection use*Note 1: It is not recommended to unravel / unbraid the grenade without expertise in re-braiding.*Note 2: Paracord is strong but NOT intended for mountaineering/climbingTHE FRIENDLY SWEDE - Selected Accessories:If you for any reason are not happy with any product by The Friendly Swede, please do not hesitate to contact us and will do our best to solve your problem asap!

B00H6YIZKK.title: With Sharp Eye Knife - The Friendly Swede Carabiner "Grenade" Survival Kit Pull with Needle, Wire, Alcohol Pad, Tin Foil, Tinder, Fire Starter, Fishing Lines, Fishing Hooks, Weights, Swivels, Dobber Wrapped in 9ft of 500 lb Paracord in Retail Packaging - Lifetime Warranty
B00H6YIZKK.Best review: Let us not mistake this for a real Survival “kit”. But here’s the point- too many people forget or fail to take along their ‘real kit’ as “they are just going for a day hike’ or “just going off the trail a bit” or just …”. The next line is usually  “Search parties have been organized” or worse…“Cadaver dogs found….”.So, this little gizmo is super handy in that you can carry it always (maybe not on a airplane). It has a decent little fire starter, some tinder, a blade, etc all wrapped in paracord.Fishing kit is perhaps not so great for food gathering but the line is useful and stopping to fish or start a fire will stop you from PANICING, which is so very critical. DON’T PANIC! As a wise man once said.Quality workmanship and materials too, which is nice as a lot of this stuff is cheap junk.I assume you have a whistle and flashlite on your keyring anyway, and with this you’re Ok to go “just for…”

B007QYV8OU.description: Features: Specially-designed for different purposes like military, law enforcement, self-defense, hunting, outdoor, search, rescue etc. Rapid power-on and brightness adjustment by rotating the bezel control ring. Magnetically-controlled stepless brightness adjustment system. Stainless steel lens retaining ring protects against impact. Durable stainless steel lanyard hole. CREE XM-L LED with a maximum output of up to 500 lumens. New two-section curved reflector custom-designed for CREE LEDs improves reflective efficiency and focusing capability. Effective throw of over 113 meters. Newly designed high efficiency broad voltage drive circuit. Titanium pocket clip. Able to tailstand for use as a candle. Impact-resistant in accordance with US MIL-STD-810F. Waterproof in accordance with IPX-8 (2 meter submersible). Specifications: Model: RRT01, LED: CREE XM-L T6, Maximum output: 500 lumens, Reflector: Custom-designed precision metal reflector, Lens: Double-sided toughened mineral glass with anti-reflective coating, Material: Aero-grade aluminum alloy, Finish: HA III military grade hard-anodized, Battery: RCR123*1/CR123A*1, Standby current: 50μA, Switch: Rapid Response Control Ring IPX-8 standard waterproof (2 meter submersible), Dimensions: Tube diameter 23mm, Total length 81mm, Weight: 46g (without battery).
B007QYV8OU.title: JETBeam RRT01 XM-L Raptor Series Cree LED Flashlight, Grey
B007QYV8OU.Best review: I just got this light and so far I'm very pleased. It's kind of on the 'floody' side which is what I want in a light that's going to be used mostly close up. It's very bright though I don't have the tools to determine if it's actually 600 lumens.  That's right, the documentation that comes with the light claims 600 lumens, not the 500 in the listing.  Thanks to the other reviewer who mentioned that rechargable 18350 batteries would fit as they have about twice the capacity of the RCR123 cells specified in the documentation.  They are the same voltage so no problems there. Nowhere in the documentation or in the reviews I looked at mentioned if there was battery protection built into the light so you would probably be wise if using an unprotected battery to not run it until the battery is completely dead as that could kill the battery.  When I have time I'll probably test that out with a battery I don't care about.edit: The detent on the brightness ring that holds it in the "off" position is not strong enough and last night the light turned on in my pocket. This is a pretty major fault so I'm dinging the light 2 stars.  I'm dealing with it by carrying with the battery compartment unscrewed 1/4 turn to make sure it doesn't come on and run the battery down. Too bad as it's otherwise a nice light.

B000LC2PO6.description: Sierra Hand Saw, Tempered Flexible Steel Blade Cuts Smooth & Clean, Locking Blade With Unbreakable Handle, 7" Blade Length, 16" Overall Length, 9-1/2" Length Closed.
B000LC2PO6.title: Coghlans 8400 Sierra Hand Saw
B000LC2PO6.Best review: The blade doesn't stay closed on its own, and the locking mechanism to keep it locked open is pretty cheap... but.... it works! Man, does it work!  The blade is VERY sharp and it cuts through 4 to 5 inch logs in around 30 seconds.  Very nice buy!

B005N83HPE.description: AIM Sports Compact Tactical Light is a really bright idea! Get yours for LESS! Light up the night without lightening up your wallet! Tough-built Tac Light from AIM Sports is about to become your favorite go-to when you need to shed a little light on the subject. Its shadow-shattering 90-lumen beam is driven by maintenance-free LEDs, and the built-in Weaver style mount attaches it to the accessory rail of your favorite firearm in seconds. And the price is no misprint! Ready to rock: Weaver style mount; Easy-to-use pressure switch; On / off end cap; L-wrench tool included; Highly water resistant; Operates on one CR123A battery (included).; 4"l., 4 1/2 ozs.; Take your best shot. Order yours today! AIM Sports Compact Tactical Light
B005N83HPE.title: Aim Sports 90 Lumens Flashlight with Mount/Pressure Switch
B005N83HPE.Best review: While completely aluminum, the glass is dirty and scratched. The "smooth" reflector has bubbles in it. The output is less than 20 lumens and very blue!
