B007VDX6IM.title: Sunwayman V11R Cree XM-L U2 Fully Variable LED Flashlight, Black
B007VDX6IM.Best review: The really great thing about this light is that  you can use CR123's, RCR123's, Eneloops, alkaline AA's and lithium rechargable AA's. You need to buy the $21.99 AA extender tube (on Amazon) for the 3 types of AA's, but that's a lot of versatility. Also, it's very hard to accidentily turn this light on. Good EDC light.

B0018X257E.description: With all the features of our best-selling Specialist glove, the Elite Winter Specialist offers critical hand protection for officers working in cold weather climates.
B0018X257E.title: Hatch Elite Winter Specialist Glove
B0018X257E.Best review: bought these gloves for winter driving and for on-duty work.they are soft and have good grip on the palm side (leather), while being smooth and sleek on the back.I really like the leather clasp that keeps wind/snow out of the wrist area.decent flexibility, but could have a little more stretch to them.I have average length fingers, with slightly thicker fingers (size 10.5 ring), and these in Large - fit great without much excess finger extra length.for warmth, they are perfect for driving, going in/out of buildings etc..  but I recently worked a 4 hour outdoor job while it was 10 degrees, and my fingers did get cold and stiff by hour 3.not for log and really cold extended use, but for most folks I would recommend them.

B0018PW5OA.description: The Energizer Weatheready 4-LED Safety Flashlight is dependable, and has a 65 hour run times.  Can operate on three different types of batteries: AA, AAA or C. Adjustable shock cord lanyard with alert whistle, and packed with 2AA Energizer Max Alkaline batteries, allows you to begin use immediately. We've included a safety preparedness checklist to help you plan, prepare and protect yourself during an emergency.
B0018PW5OA.title: Energizer Weather Ready 4 LED Flashlight With Optional Size Batteries
B0018PW5OA.Best review: Seventeen lumens sounded like a respectable amount of light. A lumen is a measure of light output in all directions. Another measure, lux, measures light output in a single direction. Since a flashlight, unlike a street light, concentrates light in one direction, a better measure would have been lux. I'll wager the lux measure for this light is low. The light is dim. At about 10 feet from a wall, it makes a weak, small, circular spot about 2 1/2 feet in diameter. In a darkened garage, objects at twenty feet away are marginally identifiable. The touted emergency checklist may be okay for cub scouts, but it's just for show in real life.The emergency whistle is okay, but in a real emergency I would prefer to have enough light to see what's going on instead of whistling in the dark.

B001P6FTHC.description: 5026This fuse block takes 12 fast acting ATO/ATC fuses and provides a connection block for negative connections too.  The cover snaps on and off and gives a location for the write-on labels (included) or preprinted labels (available as an accessoryA single sample 15 Amp fuse is included but otherwise fuses are not included with this product
B001P6FTHC.title: Blue Sea Systems 5026 ST Blade Fuse Block with Cover
B001P6FTHC.Best review: This a a great product.  I went to West Marine, and this same product was almost $60.  I use this on my 231 Mako boat and love it.  Easy to use: just add your power and ground wires to the labeled connectors.  You can change each of the fuse amps individually, to make them customized for what you want to hook up to it.  Every part of this was simple, even for a novice like me.I had an overload just this week on the boat, and the fuse popped just like it should, so I can report that it works  :-)

B00A1ZUFSG.description: Features and Specifications:- Cree XP-G2 LED with a lifespan of 20+ years of run time.- Uses one 1.5V AA battery.- Max output: 169 lumens with XP-G2.- Working voltage: 0.9V-3V- 93.5mm (Length) x 19mm (Diameter).- 63.5g weight (without battery).- Reverse polarity protection design to protect from improper battery installation.- Tail-switch and twisting head design.- Toughened ultra-clear glass lens with anti-reflective coating.- OP reflector gives perfect flood.- Removable clip.- Stand on tail to serve as a candle, with the wand covered on the head.Operation:Turn ON/OFFPress down and release the tail-switch to turn the flashlight on/off1.Switch ON: Press the tail cap button down completely until a "click" sound is heard and flashlight turns on.2.Switch OFF: Press the tail cap button down until a "click" sound is heard and the light is turned off. You also could turn the head loose a bit to turn the light off from on.Changing Modes:Method1: Half press the tail switch when the light is on to circle through firefly, low and high.Method 2: When the light is on, loosen the head a bit until the light turns off and tighten it in 2 seconds to change modes.Method 3: Click the tail switch to change modes (Interval between two clicks should be less than 2 seconds)Memory function:Memory function is activated after 2 seconds from the light turned off.Turn on the light after 2 seconds,the mode output keeps the same as your last use.
B00A1ZUFSG.title: ThruNite® T10/T10S/T10T 169 Lumen Single CREE XP-G2 LED EDC Flashlight
B00A1ZUFSG.Best review: Good Titanium light that has good output for a single AA light.  The titanium construction should provide better surface finish wear compared to anodized aluminum but inferior heat dissipation.  Seems to be a well constructed light with heavy walls and solid construction.

B00938T182.description: Maglite, Black, 2 "AAA", LED Mini Flashlight, 84 Lumens, 5 Hour 45 Minute Run Time, 141 Meter Beam Projection, Rotate The Head For On/Off & Flood To Spot Focus Feature, Anodized Aircraft Quality Aluminum, O-Ring Sealed At All Threaded Joints, Includes Flashlight, 2 "AAA" Batteries & A Pocket Clip, Perfect Size For Pocket.
B00938T182.title: Mag Instrument SP32016 BLK 2AAA LED Flashlight
B00938T182.Best review: Maglite has been redone with newer and improved LEDs. The 2 AAA model has this new model, which provides a much improved flashlight over the old model.It is well made, a classic Maglite construction, and overall a great small flashlight.I carry this one in my pocket most of the time.Any flaws with it would be issues with the design. There are not hidden features. It is round, black, twist the head to turn it on and focus, and it has a candle mode where one can remove the head and use it as a base. This feature is useful, especially with these new LEDs, during power outages and similar situations.The clip in the photo comes off. I do not use it. But I think this model was originally designed for medical professionals, who would keep them in their shirt pocket, so that makes sense to have.

B0042324M8.description: We have searched extensively in order to bring you the very best strikers for flint and steel fire starting. Our authentically styled flint strikers are forged exclusively for Wilderness Solutions by master blacksmith Shel Browder, using 18th century technology. These exquisitely finished strikers not only throw hot sparks, their smaller size allows them to fit more neatly in most tinder boxes. Each Flint and Steel Set comes with a striker, flint, a roll of charcloth and jute nesting fiber.
B0042324M8.title: Flint and Steel Kit
B0042324M8.Best review: If you are headed for the rain forest or the beach and need a sure way to light a fire this is it!  It's a light weight kit that along with your swim suit  or lack of same can trundle along in your pocket or pack and not even be noticed.  The dry jute starts a good hot fire that can even light semi damp drift wood.

B005EA09WK.description: Survival Fishing Kit - Compact Survival Fishing KitSurvival Fishing Kit is small, lightweight, and compact. The line winder enables a firm and comfortable grip that allows positive control of the line. The kit comes in a strong durable heavy duty resealable plastic bag. The bag allows room to add additional lures and tackle if you wish. The lures will give you a great chance at catching fish as quickly as possible.The kit comes with instructions on how to tie the 118 foot line, with drawings, and how to attach the weights. The kit also includes two lures, two weights, two swivels, and two hooks.
B005EA09WK.title: Survival Fishing Kit - Compact Kit For Campers/Hikers (10 Pieces)
B005EA09WK.Best review: First thing, I thought I had already written a review on this.  According to the Wonderful World of Amazonia(tm), I haven't.  Alas...As my review says, It's nothing to write home about.  In fact, it's barely enough to write a review about.  I think this is the first product I've bought that I'm having second thoughts about.  Yeah, I'll keep it because I do have it and I bought it and the seller did not misrepresent themselves.  I know I could have done a better job had I just gone to the local sporting goods store and put together a kit of my own.I'll say this, if it's a British Navy kit, it's PROBABLY for more for salt water than fresh.  Unless the Royal Navy is floating up the Thames, Don or Dee, I don't believe they've much use for a fresh water Navy.  (This comes from a career US Navy sailor who lived in the UK for five wonderfully misspent years in my late teens/early twenties courtesy of all you fine tax payers while I was on my first tour in the Navy. B00A8IKCVQ.description: With performance that well exceeds that of previous Fenix PD32 models, the UE drills through the darkness at extended distances. B00A8IKCVQ.Best review: I have collected and tested over 40 tactical and high-performance LED flashlights, and in many ways, the Fenix PD32 Ultimate Edition is simply one of the best.At 5 1/2" in length, and 1" in diameter, it fits nicely and feels comfortable in your hand. These will let you get maximum battery life from the flashlight.The 3400mAh battery will give you even better performance than the rated run times tested by Fenix with a standard 18650 battery: a full hour at 740 lumens, 2 hours 40 minutes at 400 lumens, 7 hours 15 min at 140 lumens, 27 hours at 40 lumens and 130 hours at 9 lumens.740 lumens is a LOT of light! B000I4JG26.description: Hailing from the famed firearm manufacturer, the Smith & Wesson Galaxy 13 flashlight is an ideal choice for aviators, law enforcement, hunters, campers, and members of the military. The Galaxy 13 is made from tough anodized aluminum, with 10 white LEDs (for general illumination) and three red LEDs (for seeing in the dark without losing your natural night vision). The white LEDs handle the heavy lifting, with a 30-hour battery life via three AAA batteries (included). The red LEDs, meanwhile, are particularly valuable for situations where you don't want to disturb a driver but still need to read a map, or when you're hunting in the early morning hours but don't want to attract too much attention. The red LEDs--which last for up to 80 hours on a single set of batteries--are popular among pilots, astronomers, truck drivers, military personnel, and police officers. The flashlight, which comes with a deluxe holster, carries a limited lifetime warranty.The Beam distance for the White is 17.1 meters and Red is 16.5 meters.

B0014ECZTU.description: Even if you haven't witnessed a disaster firsthand, you've seen the devastation they cause and you know that you can never be too prepared. They have a five year shelf life and are USCG approved so you know you can count on them when you need them.200 Calories per bar/4 packs of 12 bars.
B0014ECZTU.title: Datrex Emergency Survival 2400 Calorie Food Ration Bar (Pack of 4), 48 Bars
B0014ECZTU.Best review: I read the review & thought I'd risk it.  Placed a double order (8 packs) 96 bars total.  There are 12 bars to a vacuum sealed foil pack.  4 packs per order.  5 Year Shelf Life.Issue 1 - Damaged Foil - All of the seals seem OK, save one pack that has been impacted and punctured.  Looks like an ice pick hit it!  All Amazon Packaging was ok, so the puncture must have been at Datrex.  I requested a replacement pack - we'll see if I get it.Issue 2 - Shelf Life - All 8 packs were manufactured in May 2012.  They were nearly 11 months old when I received them.  Effectively, these are only good for 4 years.Bottom line: For $18.69 per order (Amazon free shipping price) I was hoping for a wee bit more in product packaging & shelf life.  They're OK.  But for $38.38 I could have purchased 4 of those $10 bricks of energy bars at Costco and packed them away long enough to last 4 years.  If I had to do it over, I'd invest my money elsewhere...should have bought another #10 can...

B001DZPEDE.description: The Bust A Cap is a one-of-a-kind one-of-a-kind device that attaches to your existing flashlight or baton and gives you a tactical advantage to break glass.  Bust A Cap is a rapid entry tool that was designed by a 13-year veteran of one of the largest Sheriffs Departments in the United States.  This device is being utilized by law enforcement, fire departments, government agencies, private security and civilians around the world, giving them a tactical and safe entry or exit out of an automobile, house, boat or plane.  Replace the existing cap on your flashlight or baton with a new Bust A Cap device.  It is now ready when you are.  The cap is manufactured in the United States and made from special steel, installs in less than a minute, requires no training and will break glass with one tap.  Bust A Cap can save your life and the lives of others. There is no way you can break a window with these flashlights without causing damage to your light or injuring someone from flying glass.  Attaching Bust A Cap to your flashlight will insure that it will break glass with just one tap and not damage your equipment.

B0068I5K4E.title: JETBeam BC25 XML Cree LED Flashlight, Black
B0068I5K4E.Best review: I have a bunch of Fenix lights and decided to try the Jetbeam BC-25 as a more affordable alternative. The construction and feel of the Jetbeam is very high quality and almost near the Fenix in fit and function. The BC-25 uses only 2-CR123 compared to 4-CR123's in the Fenix TK35 but boy was I impressed the first time I put the Jetbeam into high mode. Although the TK-35 outputs a higher lumen rating, the difference is not as noticeable as you would think and the Jetbeam is very bright! I was so impressed that I ordered a 2nd BC-25 less than 2-weeks later!The color of the BC-25 LED is also whiter than the natural tint of the Fenix TK35 which is a plus and the two BC-25's are consistent in terms of color temperature and output between the two units which speaks volumes for Jetbeams quality.Fit and finish of the BC-25 is high quality with my only note being that the tactical "ring" spins freely and appears to be made of plastic. Another thing to note that others have commented on is the two settings of the BC-25 (low and high); I would have liked to have a strobe or SOS function for emergency situations but for the price and output, one can't complain!Overall I'm very pleased with the Jetbeam and keep one in an EDC kit in the trunk of the car and the other for use around the home.Great product and I'm very impressed with my first Jetbeam purchase.

B001CUL4EI.description: This small 2 AA flashlight was designed for consumers and police departments, who want the extreme brightness and distance of the latest LED technology, yet aren’t comfortable with the cost of CR123 batteries. This new CREE LED Flashlight is fully regulated which means the brightness you see with fresh batteries is the brightness you’ll see just before batteries are depleted. Special circuitry stores power from the batteries and then delivers just the right amount to the bulb to maintain maximum brightness. At 100 lumens, the CREE LED flashlight is brighter than most 5 D battery flashlights, yet runs on the included 2 AA batteries for up to 2 hours. Consumers using 2 AA Lithium batteries can expect up to 10 hours of run time. The light also includes a removable pocket clip, wrist lanyard and a holster in addition to the 2 AA batteries. A true tactical tail cap switch allows users to twist all the way for constant on, or simply back off a half twist for momentary mode. Then, when you’re ready to put the light away, another half twist allows the light to safely be stored without worries of accidental illumination. This light is sure to be at the top of many wish lists this year.
B001CUL4EI.title: Smith and Wesson Galaxy Elite 2 AA CREE Tactical Flashlight
B001CUL4EI.Best review: I've been looking to replace my tactical flashlight that uses expensive "123 lithium batteries.This tactical flash is my answere to all.With affordable "AA" size batteries or rechargable ones, I can use this flashlight more often.Durable alum.case,with carrying pouch that holds extra battery,a wrist strap,w/ belt clip, very versatile.And of course the most important part is the light...very bright compare to the others that cost hundreds of dollars more.I like it so much that Im planning of ordering another one soon.Thank you.

B001K3HJXM.description: The Fenix LD01 is extremely small, not much bigger than the AAA cell it uses. It has 3 modes: primary, low, and maximum. It's compact size and lightweight build, it is perfect for Every Day Carry (EDC). Moreover, its solid reliability has been strictly tested and proven.       • Cree Premium (Q5) 7090 XR-E LED with lifespan of 50,000 hours • Three output types: 27 Lumens (3.5hrs) -> 10 Lumens (8.5hrs) -> 80 Lumens (1hr) • Uses one 1.5V AAA (Alkaline, Ni-MH, Lithium) battery, inexpensive and widely available • 75mm (length) x 14mm (Diameter) • Made of durable aircraft-grade aluminum • Durable Type III hard-anodized anti-abrasive finish • 14.8-gram weight (excluding batteries) • Waterproof to IPX-8 Standard • Toughened ultra-clear glass lens with anti-reflective coating • Reliable twist switch • Capable of standing up securely on a flat surface to serve as a candle • Included accessories: clip, key ring, and a spare O-ring

B001K3HJXM.Best review: This is about the size of a Case Stockman pocket knife, and is about as useful. I keep mine in my pocket all the time and use it every morning so I know what color shirt I'm getting out of the closet. I get more use out of this than I do my pocket knife, so If I had to leave on at home...Really, this is a good value and handy too. You can get a shiny stainless steel one for about $15 more, which might have a more durable finish. Maybe.Twists on and off. Maybe 1/10 of a turn required. Easy to do one-handed.

B00ANY4EXM.description: Even if you haven't witnessed a disaster firsthand, you've seen the devastation they cause and you know that you can never be too prepared. B00ANY4EXM.title: Datrex Emergency Survival Water Pouch (Pack of 64), 125ml
B00ANY4EXM.Best review: These were ordered for emergency packs for the car. They were perfect for what we needed and anyone making anything emergency related.

B004GAVOUU.description: Mora Craftline Series feature sharp, durable utility knives suitable for construction, trade and industrial professionals. B004GAVOUU.title: Morakniv Craftline Q Allround Fixed Blade Utility Knife with Sandvik Carbon Steel Blade, 3.8-Inch

The edge retention has been great, and the knife is comfortable.The sheath is okay, but no worries there.  As long as its not COMPLETE junk, then its alright.Back to the knife, this is the first Mora we've owned and we are completely satisfied with it. B0002IXQLK.description: New files can also be purchased in Spyderco four-packs (sold separately).This set of four fine-grit ceramic files, stored neatly in an included leather carrying pouch, helps maintain your cutlery and debur hardened tools, molds, and even carbide. The set includes a round, square, triangular, and slip-shaped -- or teardrop -- file, which can be easily cleaned with a plastic scouring pad and powdered abrasive cleaner. Made in the USA, the set is autoclave safe.WarrantySypderco products include a limited manufacturer's warranty against defects in materials and workmanship. Details are included with your purchase.About SpydercoThinking beyond established knife industry practices has allowed Spyderco to introduce new innovations, including one-hand opening, serrations on a folder, and a clip to attach a knife to a pocket. Spyderco remains dedicated to researching and developing improved, better-performing materials with function and reliability, and its unique cutlery line is a result of designing ergonomic, functional tools. The company puts its new products through rigorous testing prior to release, examining edge retention with a CATRA machine, looking for rust development with Q-FOG, checking the force needed to open and close a knife, and analyzing numerous other technical details.
B0002IXQLK.title: Spyderco Ceramic File 4 Piece Set w/ Leather Pouch
B0002IXQLK.Best review: I bought this to sharpen profiled plane blades; mostly for plane blades used in Stanley's combination planes. They have been excellent for that purpose.  I bought them at a specialty retail store for the same price offered here.  I would recommend them for this purpose as the triangular file and round file are perfect fits for the profiles I have sharpened so far. It is a good idea to get your hand honing skills up to speed when using these as you can't really use a jig because of their size and the profiles of the blades I sharpen.  I bought the fine grade set, and I'd like to see a medium and extra fine set as well.  The addition of the two sets would make sharpening much faster.The files cut quickly in the steel used for the plane blades. I was surprised.  I've never used ceramic before just oil and water stones, sandpaper and diamonds. I have a diamond hone, but it didn't work as well as the files did on these plane blades, and it was too large for some of the profiles (it's a 600 grit thing with a red plastic handle).The produce a near mirror finish on the bevels of the blades I've been sharpening.  I think the extra fine would yield a mirror finish.

B0091TRPVI.description: The Fenix E25 Flashlight is a compact, lightweight and waterproof to IPX-8 standard, brilliant addition to every toolbox from the professional outdoorsman to the hobbyist. It features an anti-roll, slip-resistant body design capable of standing up securely on a flat surface to serve as a candle. Powered by two AA batteries, Fenix E25 delivers a max 187-lumen output and 156-meter throw. The All-function switch on the head gives you total control of the light. Activating the light or choosing an ideal output is simple and intuitive. AA batteries, Campmor item #82760.Low power indication with over discharge protection.Premium Type III hard-anodized anti-abrasive finish.Reflector with high efficiency and focus for far throw and wide lighting range.Reverse polarity protection to protect from improper battery installation.Toughened ultra-clear glass lens with anti-reflective coating.Waterproof to IPX-8 Standard.Includes: Lanyard, Spare O-Rings , Rubber Switch Boot.Made of durable aircraft-grade aluminum.Battery: Two AA batteries (NOT INCLUDED).Weight: 4.25 oz with batteries.Weight: 2.6 oz.1"- 6".
B0091TRPVI.title: Fenix E25 Flashlight
B0091TRPVI.Best review: I loved the very long throw of this light, but it's case is a little long for my use, and I wanted the lighter weight and higher power density of a LION battery, so bought the E35. Unfortunately, the E35 has a BAD doughnut hole artifact that leaves what you're pointing it at in the dark.Bottom line, I'm probably going to keep the E25 and return the E35. They're both good lights though, so I hate to return either of them, but of the two, this one has a MUCH better beam pattern, and I can't say I notice the few meters of advertised throw I give up with the E25.I guess I'll just have to buy some high-end AA NiMh cells, and put up with the extra weight on my bicycle helmet. The issue there is neck strain on long rides.If you haven't used a Fenix light, and want one with a very tight beam, you're in for a real treat with this light. For reference, IIRC, a 6 D-Cell MagLite with a Xeon bulb is about 80 lumens. You can get that much light out of an LD01, powered by a single AAA cell. I have one, and 3 other Fenix lights. You'll be spoiled for life.

B004IF5ZDA.description: Energizer Hard Case Tactical ROMEO LED Compact Vest light provides hands-free use. With an easy push button tail-switch to regulate brightness with the touch of a finger, it will shine up to 43 lumens. Rugged design features a water resistant, aircraft-grade aluminum alloy body, shatterproof lens and nearly indestructible LED. This light is waterproof up to one Meter for 30 minutes. Red and blue lens covers offer versatile light options for tracking and night vision and easily screw into tail cap for storage. Pocket clip is attached for positioning and runs on 1 AA Energizer Ultimate Lithium battery (included)
B004IF5ZDA.title: Energizer Hard Case Tactical ROMEO 1-LED Compact Vest Light (Batteries Included)
B004IF5ZDA.Best review: This is a lightweight, short range light.  This is not a 600+ lumen searchlight but it is perfect for 80% of my needs.  It fits perfectly on my pack straps and provides just enough light forward to see what I'm working with and what's in my direct surroundings.The color-lenses REALLY knock down the output so don't expect to be able to use them for distance work but they work great if you need to just read something in the dark or quickly scan the ground for a blood trail in the dark.

B00DITWQMA.description: Fenix proves that it doesn't take a big light to make big light. The PD35 Flashlight throws a huge 850 lumen beam, even though it's only 5. 5 inches long and weighs three ounces. That's at its maximum setting (called 'Turbo'). there are four other settings, and they drop in light output as they increase in battery life. The lowest setting produces 10 lumens and shines for a whopping 140 hours.
B00DITWQMA.title: Fenix PD35 Flashlight
B00DITWQMA.Best review: Bought this light to replace my TK15.  I liked the TK15 but over time the brightness button became erratic in which the brightness would flicker between bright and dim.  The PD35 is smaller, seems to have a sturdier brightness button, is brighter, and a little lighter to carry.  Plus the beam has no 'rings' and a bigger center spotlight.  Its not as good as a Surefire beam which transitions from spotlight to floodlight more gradually, but its not bad.  I work on planes and needed a good inspection light at night and this fits the bill as mentioned plus it uses 123's or 18650 battery, and has the double ended spring like the TK15 to let the battery 'float'.  We'll see how it does in the long run.6-2014Almost a year and the light is still working, nothing broke and everything functions as usual.  Dropped it a few times so it has some small scratches and dings on it.  Rubber brightness button works without malfunctioning and the rubber hasnt deteriorated or broken off yet.

B000NRPQM2.description: The Petzl TIKKA XP is at the cutting edge of high-output hands-free-lighting. Though it weighs just over 3 ounces, this headlamp still blasts out up to 35 lumens to a distance of up to 114 feet. It gives you a lot of flexibility in terms of lighting options, too. You get three different lighting levels (maximum, optimum, and economic) and two beam options (flood and spot) for short- and long-range illumination. Plus, if you really need to see what's making that growling noise way up ahead on the trail, it features a boost mode that increases output to 40 lumens for a 160-foot range beam (boost mode automatically shuts off after 20 seconds to conserve energy). And if you get lost running away from whatever was growling at you, it also includes an emergency strobe mode that makes you easy to locate.The TIKKA XP will last up to 120 on the three included AAA batteries. If you do get toward the end of your charge, a battery level indicator lets you know when the batteries are 70% and 90% discharged. The Petzl TIKKA XP comes with a comfortable elastic headband and three AAA batteries. Three-year guarantee.--Josh DettweilerWhat's in the BoxHeadlamp with strap, headstrap, 3 AA/LR6 batteries
B000NRPQM2.title: Petzl E86 PR Tikka XP Headlamp, Red
B000NRPQM2.Best review: I install satellite systems and wanted a quality headlamp for the crawl spaces.  I was pretty impressed with its brightness and construction.  I'd buy 2 more but the cost is significant although well worth it for one if you are going to use it on a regular bases, which you will if you have it.  I don't want to purchase 3 of them so I just carry it with me.  i use it when installing appliances instead of carrying a flashlight.  Flashlights take one of your hands and are usually larger.  This fits in a small cell phone pocket on my tool pouch.

B000NP6NP8.description: Lightweight sports styling contour to the face to provide maximum protection. Vented lens allows air to flow away from the lens to prevent fogging. Adjustable nose pad provides a comfortable fit for a broad range of bridge sizes. Anti-Scratch lenses offer 99% protection against harmful UV rays.
B000NP6NP8.title: Pyramex Fortress Safety Eyewear
B000NP6NP8.Best review: Looks great, light weight! Very useful as eye protection from wind and dust on bicycles and motobikes as well. highly recommended

B004R5V47C.description: Every Elzetta ZSM comes with Sizing Adapters, giving the Flashlight Mount the ability to hold flashlights from 0.70 to 1.05 Inch in diameter (18 to 27 mm). The Elzetta ZSM is designed for 12-Gauge Shotguns and also comes with Gauge Adapters that allow the Elzetta ZSM to be used with 20-Gauge and.410 shotguns. When installed correctly, the Elzetta ZSM will not move under recoil nor allow the flashlight to move.
B004R5V47C.title: Elzetta Tactical Shotgun Flashlight Mount
B004R5V47C.Best review: It's sturdy and light and puts the flashlight in a great spot. As has been stated before, you can easily over-tighten the screws on the tube. Make sure to function test after installation.

B0000950Q9.description: The Tikka headlamp features three super-bright white LEDs each offering a different brightness setting of high, medium, and low. A fourth bulb functions as a long-lasting strobe light perfect for roadside emergencies and as reliable bike light that evening commute. The Tikka Plus is water resistant and won't short out even if submerged. Burn times for the four light settings (High, Medium, and Low) are: 80 hours, 120 hours, and 150 hours on a single battery pack. And, the strobe light burns for up to 400 hours. Best of all, the Tikka Plus is small enough for the pocket, the glove box, or the toolbox for convenient, reliable lighting when you need it most. More great features: A tilting lamp let's you aim the beam at the trail in front of you, so you don't have to keep your neck cocked at an uncomfortable angle. A large anti-glare lip lets you aim the light where you want without blinding your buddy with peripheral glare. And, an easy access, push-button switch is recessed so that it doesn't accidentally turn on as you slam the suitcase shut. Your purchase includes three AAA batteries.
B0000950Q9.title: Petzl Tikka Plus 4-LED Headlamp #E47P
B0000950Q9.Best review: I live in the Northeast and run all year long in a local park with no lighting on the running path. During the winter months it can be tricky to run by just moonlight. I needed a lightweight, stable, and effective headlamp. After doing much research I bought the Tikka Plus, and am very happy with it.Unlike other models, there are no wires dangling. It is easily adjustable to fit around my head and does not slip or bounce around at all while I run. This is also one of the lightest headlamps, and is barely noticeable on my head. The tilt feature and adjustable light easily illumine the running path. Usually the medium setting is sufficient(there are high, medium, and low settings, a strobe, and also a high intensity setting).The direction brochure is not the best, but with a little experimenting you will see that you do not have to cycle through all of the settings each time you use this.This product does everything it is supposed to and I highly recommend it.

B001IABX3Y.description: Night Hike? Go ahead. If you've got your glow-in-the-dark compass with you, you can find your way back without having to grope around trying to feel the moss on the north side of the trees. In brass, 2-Inch dia by 1/2-Inch thick, with a bezel with 2-degree increments and a 13/16-Inch dia hook on top.
B001IABX3Y.title: SE CC50B Glow-in-the-Dark Brass Compass
B001IABX3Y.Best review: This item is a great-looking prop, especially if paired with something likethis inexpensive quality pocket watch chain. It isn't suitable as a toy for young children in my opinion, since it is oil-filled and does contain tiny amounts of a poisonous chemical that could be accessed if the case were chewed open.Mine also pointed north as checked with my Casio Pathfinder.I probably wouldn't work inside a car or a metal train carriage because *IT'S A SIX DOLLAR PROP*If you want to navigate under adverse conditions pay for a compass that is designed for the purpose.Sweet Azathoth on a bike, what do some of these reviewers expect for this kind of money?

B0006GWRJK.description: Easy, do-it-yourself kit, molds in 10 minutes. Dozens of everyday uses including shooting sports, sporting events, construction, lawn care, assembly lines, farming, auto races, swimming, flying, factories and much more!.Note: Best before 12 months from date of manufacture.
B0006GWRJK.title: Radians Custom Molded Earplugs
B0006GWRJK.Best review: The end result of these is amazing.  Comfortable fit, great noise protection (from my snoring wife), and they don't get shoved deeper into my ears when I lay down on them like the normal foam ones do.  The process of mixing the two putties together was easy, and fitment into my ears was a breeze.The only downside---the curing process.  About 2 minutes into the curing in your ear, they start making this really weird popping noise and you can feel air bubbles escaping around your ear canal.  It's the most bizarre sensation I can imagine, it's like there's popcorn being popped inside your head.  This said, it's only for about 15 minutes as they cure pretty quick, then you can take them out and it's fine from then on out.It's not a downside that would stop me from using them, but it's definitely a consideration for people with really sensitive ears or eardrums.  It's reasonably loud as it's literally inside of your ear.  If these were to fail at some point, I would still do the process over as the payoff of comfortable earplugs easily outweighs the brief discomfort of the curing process.

B001CNQQ8O.description: This is one credit card that could literally save your life. The new Tool Logic Survival Card is packed with lifesaving features. Features include: 2" Serrated Blade, Loud Signal Whistle, Tweezer & toothpick, Lanyard hole, Compass, and 8x Power Lens.
B001CNQQ8O.title: Tool Logic Survival Card
B001CNQQ8O.Best review: I had gotten some of these for my wife and son as part of a small kit for when skiing. I was impressed with the tools and construction I got one for myself. The whistle is nice and loud and the fire starter works well. The weak point is the compass. It doesn't seem to work very consistantly.

B003UNVD5K.description: Compact, portable and durable, this area light serves many  needs. Take this area light along with you and mount to any metal surface with its strong magnets. Or secure the included mounting plate to a wall for a fixed light you can remove and take with you easily. Protected by a tough rubber over mold, the light can survive a 3 Meter drop. Operation is easy, even with gloved hands. Just press the lens to activate.
B003UNVD5K.title: Energizer Hard Case Professional 3-LED Puck Light (Batteries Included)
B003UNVD5K.Best review: I bought these to go along with my purchase ofSterilite 4-Shelf Shelving Unit, Platinum. Set up was easy-just remove the outer rubber sleeve, install the included batteries and let it rip. For my use I wedged the energizer light in the spaced ribs under one of the shelves just to see if I needed mounting and how it fit. One small strip of DS Velcro and it's ready to go.The push On/Off works great, and the included batteries saved me a few $. Highly recommend and if a storm comes up I'm ready.

B006K5C2EG.description: iTP A3 LED flashlight is designed for everyday use. It is small enough to be used as a key so you carry it with you everywhere. Its AAA battery, which is less expensive and easy to get, adds additional values.It is the upgraded version of the iTP A3 model.Features and Specifications:LED: Cree R5, life span up to 50000 hoursFinish: HA Type ⅢReflector: Aluminum alloyMax output level: 96 lumensOperating voltage: 0.9V - 3.0VBattery: 1 x AAA, 1 x Rechargeable NiMh AAA, or 1 x 10440 (Due to the small light body size,10440 batteries are not recommended since it may cause the light become hot very quickly.)Size: Length 66.5 mm *Diameter 14 mm,Weight: 9g (excluding battery and keychain), 17g(excluding battery)Upgrade Edition: Three output levels - Low 1.5 lumens (50 hours) ->Medium 18 lumens (4 hours) ->-High 96 lumens (55 minutes)
B006K5C2EG.title: iTP A3 EOS 96 Lumen Flashlight -Upgrade Version 1 X AAA battery
B006K5C2EG.Best review: There are many very positive reviews on this flashlight, I found the same pro's and con's as others.What can I add?This is a tiny flashlight, the flashlight itself about the size of a AA battery. The AA battery is 2 inch long and the flashlight is 2 3/4 inch long. It use's a AAA battery to produce a very powerful beam of light. Perfect size to keep on a key chain (comes with a easy to use key chain attachment).I have used both the AAA standard battery and the 10440 rechargeable battery in this flashlight. What I found,  although the 10440 does provide a little more light the flashlight itself does get very hot - quickly. So I don't use the 10440 anymore as the AAA provides a amazing amount of light. The 10440 battery is not necessary but it is nice to know it can be an alternative power source.One useful feature is the three levels of power settings this light has. A low, med and high setting. To cycle just twist the head of the light on and off, every time you do that it goes up one power level. So if you don't need the full power of light say just lighting a keyhole, you don't have to, adding to the longevity of the batteries.I highly recommend this flashlight, everyone should have one on their key chain.

B001GAOOAK.description: The Fenix L1D LED flashlight is digitally regulated and digitally controlled. It has two output modes which produce a total of six levels of output. These modes not only allow the user to select the best compromise between brightness and runtime for any given task, but they also help to aid in an emergency. The L1D does all this and still retains a very compact size. If you're looking for solid reliability, digitally-regulated brightness, and compact size, this Fenix is for you.
B001GAOOAK.title: Fenix L1D 6 Level High Performance Cree LED Flashlight
B001GAOOAK.Best review: This is a great light. For something that just uses 1xaa battery this is extremely bright.It has 4 light settings plus an SOS and strobe setting. When the bezel is fully tightened you click it once and you get turbo mode, soft tap the button and it will change to strobe. Click it again to turn the light off. If you loosen the bezel a little the light will give you 4 more modes. Low - Medium - High - SOS.This light does not let you program the modes like some do, but I find that this light does everything I need.The build quality is great. It has a nice solid feel to it. The clicky switch is nice and sturdy, although it is somewhat noisy.Overall I really like this light. For more details I recommend going to youtube and looking for a review by nutnfancy.The only thing this light is missing is a pocket clip. It comes with a lanyard but I prefer a pocket clip. As far as I know Fenix does not offer a clip for this light. Right now I am using a clip from a Gerber Infinity Ultra. It fits pretty well.

B000B8JDT0.description: The versatile, compact Quick Fix sharpener, from cutlery sharpening company Lansky, combines two sharpening technologies -- tungsten carbide to hone the blade to a fine point, and ceramic to smooth the edge for a long-lasting keen. A molded rubber grip ensures solid, slip-free use, and it takes only three or four strokes to get your blade razor-sharp. Best of all, you can take it with you anywhere, as it stows easily in your pocket, tackle box, daypack, briefcase, or purse.WarrantyThis Lansky product includes a limited one-year manufacturer's warranty against defects in materials and workmanship.
B000B8JDT0.title: Lansky Quick Fix Pocket Sharpener (colors may vary)
B000B8JDT0.Best review: I didn't buy this through Amazon but I did purchase one of these sharpeners regardless.  Best part?  It is made in America!  I just sharpened ALL my kitchen knives with this sharpener.  I decided to try and sharpen an old razor knife just to see what it would do.  I didn't have any expectations with it, however, it sharpened my razor knife back to its originating blade.  I am crazy in love with this sharpener!  Only thing I would recommend is to run your blade through one way and then the opposite way just to keep the blade sharp.  My garden sheers are now too sharp for me (if that's possible).  I cannot recommend this sharpener enough...especially for the price.

B003UTX0R8.description: DuPont Non-Stick with Teflon Fluoropolymer is a unique dry-film lubricant made of 100% Teflon and surface binding agents. Dry lubricant will repel abrasive contaminants while lubricating. Formulated with Teflon for longer lubricant life, enhanced wear protection, better high and low temperature range and increased resistance to water. Use on surfaces requiring a dry, non-oily, non-staining, silicone-free film. Effective from -100°F to 480°F (-73°C to 250°C). Use on cutting surfaces such as saw blades, drill bits or on flat surfaces such as table saws. Works to lubricate tight tolerance gears or flat sliding surfaces such as treadmills.
B003UTX0R8.title: DuPont Teflon Non-Stick Dry-Film Lubricant Aerosol Spray, 10 Oz.
B003UTX0R8.Best review: Works great on vinyl window tracks I've found.  Been working my way around the house, completely tearing down my windows for a thorough cleaning inside and out, along with the track and weeping holes.  A few sprays on the track and where the window contacts the frame, and slides like new.

B000J5JCHI.description: This item comes with well known brand name of Rothco. Rothco is the World's Foremost Supplier of Military and Outdoor Clothing and Accessories.
B000J5JCHI.title: Olive Drab Military GI Style C-Cell Anglehead Flashlight
B000J5JCHI.Best review: There are some rather harsh reviews out there for what is effectively a 6 dollar flashlight but overall its a pretty nice little military style light.  The C cells make me hope it lasts longer than an AA light may.  Its reasonably bright, certainly enough for a common backpack trip.  I added maglight zenon bulbs for a few bucks and made it much brighter.I like it.  Definitely worth the 6 bucks
